title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and chill several hours. Shape into small balls.
Makes about 20 to 24 balls.

title: cran-raspberry slush
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend on high just until mixed.
Makes a nice holiday appetizer.

title: john wellis' baby ribs
directions: Rub on Dry Spices and Basting Sauce, then refrigerate ribs 3 hours prior to cooking.
Brush ribs with Sweet Sauce the last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Put Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup of water; stir and set aside. Mix remaining ingredients in a large bowl and set aside.
Heat tomato soup on medium heat until boiling, then add cream cheese, stirring constantly, until blended.
Remove from heat; stir in Knox gelatine mixture.
Let cool for 15 minutes, then add to remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold (4-cup size) and chill.

title: baked jellied grapes
directions: Wash grapes; separate skins from pulp.
Simmer pulp about 10 minutes; put through sieve.
Place skins and pulp in a 1-quart baking dish.
Add tapioca, sugar and warm water; stir lightly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir after 30 minutes, then again when finished baking.
Serve cold with whipped cream.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Cover bottom of Pyrex dish with wafers.
Pour 1 package strawberries over wafers, then half of milk; repeat.
Place wafers on top.
Let chill overnight.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and milk in large kettle.
Boil 5 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add everything but nuts.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool; cut into pieces.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni by package directions.
When done, set aside and dice meat and chop vegetables.
Mix together.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with 1/2 cup salad dressing.

title: singapore chicken barbecue
directions: In a small bowl stir together curry, sugar, soy, oil and garlic.
Place cubed chicken in a plastic bag.
Pour marinade over meat, seal and move all around to coat.
Refrigerate in bag 4 hours minimum (or up to 2 days).
Place on skewers and barbecue. Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Crisco.
Beat well.
Add eggs one at
a time.
Alternate flour with milk, adding flour last.
Add vanilla. Bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: stack-a-roll stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Pour into large casserole or pan.
Stir in mushrooms and 2/3 can of onion rings.
Heat mushroom soup and add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour on top of meat mixture.
Slice biscuits in half and place, cut side down, around edge of casserole.
Mix 1/2 cup of sour cream.
Add egg and pour over biscuits.
Add remaining onion rings to top of meat mixture in middle.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients together; pour into a 13 x 2 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts.
Form into a ball and chill. Roll ball in nuts and coat.

title: poor man's cake
directions: In large saucepan, simmer sugar, water, shortening and raisins for about 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Blend the remaining ingredients and stir into mixture.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Using a large punch bowl, divide cake in half and crumble each half.
Pack half of crumbled cake in bottom of bowl in order.
Use half of each ingredient in layers.
Pudding, coconut, pineapple, cocktail, cherries, Cool Whip; top with pecans, layer again starting with cake first then in order as first.
Refrigerate. Best if leftover night before serving.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix ingredients together.
A real good salad.
May be served on lettuce, if desired.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Prepare Jell-O.
Set aside to cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate until set.
Serves 4.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with nuts and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.

title: creamy hot beef dip
directions: Combine ingredients in a 1-quart dish.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Great for vegetable dip or spread on crackers.

title: russian dill pickles
directions: Bring sugar, water, vinegar and salt to a boil and cool. Slice cucumbers lengthwise.
Pack in jars with dill, garlic, small onion and pinch of alum.
Pour cooled brine over pickles; seal loosely.

title: sour cream chicken
directions: Place chicken in saucepan.
Add water to cover; cook gently until tender, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Place in buttered baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Crush crackers and mix with melted butter. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine and simmer 20 minutes, uncovered, then add 1/2 cup catsup and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Just bring to a boil.
Baste once or twice.
Makes about 1 3/4 cups.

title: danish pastry
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Blend with flour and salt.
Add lukewarm milk and yeast.
Mix to make dough not too hard and not too soft. Add 4 tablespoons melted butter so it won't stick.
Pat with flour all over.
Let rise for 2 hours.
Grease cookie sheets.
Place flour mixed with cinnamon on a board.
Divide dough into thin rolls and roll in mixture on board.
Cut and make pinwheels. Place on cookie sheet; let rise again 1 hour.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Tops can be punched out and filled with jam or pie filling.

title: sheath cake
directions: Mix in medium saucepan first 4 ingredients.
Bring this to a boil.
Remove from heat and add next 3 ingredients.
Mix well and add last 3 ingredients.
Just mix well and pour into a greased and floured 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Pour on icing while cake is still hot.

title: spice cake
directions: Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat on medium speed with hand mixer until well blended (do not overmix).
Bake in a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch greased and lightly floured pan at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut peppernuts from aunt susan entz
directions: Mix and roll into ropes.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces and bake 7 minutes in 400° oven.

title: bubble pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and drain.
Stir in pizza sauce. Quarter the biscuits and place in greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Top with beef mixture and your favorite toppings.
Bake uncovered at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 10 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 - 10 minutes before serving.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Blend all ingredients; chill and stir well again before serving.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, pudding mix and cocoa.
Mix together the remaining ingredients, then mix well with dry ingredients. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes in 3 round pans.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, ginger and sugar.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mixture and nuts on top.
Drizzle 1 1/2 sticks melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Put all but bark in a large bowl.
Melt the bark and pour over.
Put on wax paper by spoonfuls.

title: herbed buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve with salads or as a vegetable dip.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add frozen broccoli and onion.
Heat until soft (about 15 minutes).
Cook rice.
Combine rice, broccoli, cheese and soup.
Bake uncovered 15 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Mix flour and spices into shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in molasses and drop by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with spoon, sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool a minute before removing from pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Blend together and chill.
Good with any fresh vegetable tray.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti; drain.
Toss with butter and Parmesan cheese. Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Layer macaroni, Mozzarella cheese, meat and sauce. Sprinkle lightly with oregano.
Repeat several times until all ingredients are used.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites until stiff.
Mix other ingredients.
Stir in beaten egg whites.
Bake in waffle iron.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt margarine and add to dressing. Divide in thirds.
In a large casserole dish, place a layer of dressing, then layer of chicken.
Top with mushroom soup, mixed with 3/4 can of chicken broth.
Add another layer of dressing, then layer of chicken.
Add can of cream of chicken soup, mixed with 3/4 can chicken broth.
Top with dressing.
Bake 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: big fat fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend together dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Do not overbeat.
Spread batter into ungreased 8-inch square pan. Bake 40 to 45 minutes until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool completely.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: orange flavored coffee
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or food processor and grind until powdered.
You can substitute the appropriate amount of artificial sweetener for sugar.
Powdered creamer can be substituted for the powdered milk.
Put 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of the homemade coffee into a cup filled with hot water.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into cast-iron skillet.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 skillets of bread.
Delicious with vegetables or soups.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Heat well.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and place thin layer of sauce over bottom.
Place 6 tortillas in pan and spread remaining sauce over top.
Cover with six more tortillas.
Pour soup over top.
Pour milk over soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with fresh lettuce, tomatoes and salsa over top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix yellow corn, Niblets corn, eggs, margarine, cornbread mix and sour cream. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or less in a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 smaller pans. This can be frozen before or after baking.

title: stay soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs, salt and baking powder.
Add soda to	buttermilk
and
mix
remaining ingredients.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream sugars (brown and white), margarine and eggs.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Drop with Number 40 scoop or heaping teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs with 1 cup mashed very ripe bananas. Fold in the flour, cream of tartar, soda, salt and chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Bake 24 cupcakes as directed on box, then cool. Cut cupcakes in half after cooled.

title: chickpea soup (portuguese)
directions: Cover meat, linguica and onion with water and bring to a boil. Add the soaked dried chickpeas if you are using them.
Cook until meat is fork-tender (2 1/2 to 3 hours over medium heat).
When meat is cooked, add the peeled and chopped vegetables (and canned chickpeas if you are not using dried kind).
Add more liquid as needed while ingredients are cooking.
I drain off most of the liquid when the soup is done and cook the rice in it.
Add the sprig of spearmint for last few minutes of cooking.

title: hot dog hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut each hot dog in 3 pieces.
Cut strips of bacon to wrap around the hot dog and secure with wooden toothpick.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven until sugar melts and bacon is done.

title: spaghetti in electric skillet
directions: Heat skillet at 350°.
Melt shortening and brown vermicelli (broken into 1/4-inch pieces) to medium color.
Add meat, cook and stir.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Add hot water to cover and cook 20 minutes.
Place layer of cheese on mixture. Cover and cook 5 minutes until cheese melts.

title: the very best pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve sugar in liquids.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Check at 45 minutes.
Yields 4 small loaves or 2 large.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Beat eggs, flour and milk until smooth.
Shred cheeses.
Mix two sauces together.
In greased casserole, layer first 1/2 of cheeses and 1/2 chiles.
Repeat.
Pour milk mixture over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and pour tomato sauce mixture over top.
Bake 15 to 20 more minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix and pudding in large bowl.
Add sour cream, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix for 5 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan, which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Empty dry cake mix in bowl.
Add 1 cup nectar to oil and mix well.
Add to cake mix.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well. Pour into a greased tube pan or bundt pan. Bake at 350 degrees until cake begins to leave the sides of the pan.
Mix remaining 2/3 cup nectar with powdered sugar.
Make holes in cake with a skewer and pour nectar over hot cake.
Allow time to absorb.
Turn cake onto plate.
Make a glaze of powdered sugar and lemon juice. Spread on cake.

title: old-tyme tea cakes
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg.
Stir soda into milk, then add flour.
Roll dough out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until done.

title: praline bars
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet that has sides.
Melt margarine and sugar; boil 3 minutes.
Add nuts.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Take out of oven and quickly remove to wax paper.
Let cool completely.
Enjoy!!

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick according to box instructions. Add cheese. Cook as directed. When done, brush with garlic and melted oleo.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and margarine. Cool to lukewarm. Measure warm water into large bowl. Sprinkle in yeast and stir until dissolved. Stir in lukewarm mixture, egg and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add the rest of flour, mixing well. Place the dough in a greased bowl. Brush top with soft margarine. Cover tightly with foil or plastic wrap. Refrigerate until doubled in bulk or until needed (up to 4 days).

title: apricot surprise
directions: Cream butter and cheese into flour-baking powder mixture. Roll out.
Cut and fill with filling.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add rest of ingredients; beat until smooth.
Let cool a few minutes.
Add 1/2 pint whipping cream and beat well.
Stir in 1 can crushed pineapple or fruit cocktail. Chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: I sometimes use 1 can of whole cranberry sauce and 1 regular cranberry sauce.
I also add a small can of crushed pineapple.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each potato in half.
In a 9 x 9-inch metal pan, toss potatoes with 1 tablespoon of salad oil and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Roast potatoes for 25 minutes or until golden and tender, turning potatoes with a spatula.
Meanwhile, in saucepan, prepare macaroni as label directs; drain.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla, flour and potato chips. Drop by 1/2 teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: indulge jicama crusted chicken
directions: Pound chicken breasts until 1/2-inch thick.
Mix jicama, eggs, scallions and mustard.
Dredge chicken breast in flour and coat with jicama mixture evenly on both sides.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend for 30 seconds.

title: special baked potatoes
directions: Bake large potato; remove top and hollow out skins.
Mash and cream ingredients, adding minced onion.
Refill skins and return to oven to brown.

title: one-step angel food cake
directions: Empty dry cake mix in bowl and carefully fold in pie filling. Pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sally lunn yeast bread
directions: In a large bowl, thoroughly mix 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar, salt and undissolved active dry yeast.
Combine milk, water and margarine in a saucepan.
Heat over low heat until liquids are very warm (120° to 130°).
Margarine does not need to melt. Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour or enough flour to make a thick batter.
Beat at
high speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover; let rise in a warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour. Stir batter down and beat well, about 1/2 minute.
Turn into a well-greased and floured 9-inch tube pan.
Cover; let rise in warm place, free from draft, until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for about 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Best when served warm.
Makes 1 tube bread.

title: salad on a board
directions: Lay flat crescent rolls on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix and spread dill weed, onion, cream cheese and mayo over rolls.
Top with chopped vegetables, then sprinkle carrots and cheese on top.
Refrigerate and cut into finger-eating size pieces with a pizza cutter.

title: kahlua pig
directions: Mix all ingredients and rub onto pork.	Allow to stand 1 hour or more.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap pork in foil & place in pan. Cook 4 hours until well done.
Unwrap and shred.
In crock pot, pour mixture over pork.
Cook overnight on low heat.

title: creamy potato puffs
directions: Combine softened cheese and potatoes, mixing well. Add remaining ingredients.
Place in 1-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken fried cube steak
directions: Mix eggs with buttermilk.
Marinate steak in buttermilk for approximately 1 hour.
Drop each piece in flour and coat well. Heat vegetable oil in large electric skillet to 275°.
Fry steak to a golden brown on both sides.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix together instant pudding and milk, then add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, banana and pudding mixture.
Top with vanilla wafer crumbs and refrigerate.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown meat. Add green pepper and onion.
Add soup and spices. Simmer about 15 minutes with lid on. Cook noodles.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan. Drain noodles and place in bottom of pan.
Pour meat sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top. Arrange mushrooms over cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Remove foil and bake another 10 minutes.
Cool a little and cut into squares.

title: apple spice bars
directions: Cream shortening. Add 1 cup sugar, beating well. Add eggs, beating well. Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices in a medium mixing bowl. Gradually add to creamed mixture, stirring well. Stir in oats, apple, raisins and pecans, mixing well. Press mixture into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool on a wire rack. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into 2 x 1-inch bars. Yield: about 6 dozen.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil spaghetti, drain. Add chopped onion, chopped cucumber, bell pepper, and tomato. Mix with Italian Dressing. Add salt, pepper, and salad supreme to suit your taste. Chill and Enjoy!

title: barbecued meat patties
directions: Soak bread crumbs in 1/2 cup milk.
Add ground beef, onion, remaining milk, salt and pepper.
Form into patties.
Dip each patty into powdered sugar; brown quickly in hot fat.
Place in 8 x 8-inch baking pan.

title: black-eyed pea cornbread(one dish meal)
directions: Cook sausage and onion in large skillet. Stir until sausage is done and drain. Combine cornmeal, flour and salt. Stir together eggs, buttermilk and oil. Stir in dry ingredients until moistened; batter will not be smooth. Add sausage mixture, peas and remaining ingredients to batter, stirring well. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish for 1 hour or until golden brown. Preparation time: 35 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cornstarch and flour in saucepan.
Add milk gradually; stir until mixed.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir 1/2 cup of hot mix into egg yolks, then return to hot mixture in saucepan. Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool.
Add 1 cup coconut; pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with remaining coconut.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: syrup cake
directions: Thoroughly mix
all
of the ingredients and pour into a greased and
floured
8-inch
square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: krispie butter cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars and egg.
Mix in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add in oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and walnuts until just mixed.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake at 350° for 11 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat together thoroughly flour, sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Spread into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the bananas and vanilla wafers.
Layer with bananas and the vanilla wafers.
Chill for one hour.

title: pecan temptations
directions: Combine chocolate, milk and marshmallow cream in a double boiler.
Cook over hot water until chocolate melts, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Keep warm.
Dip each marshmallow into chocolate mixture with 2 prong fork, coating completely. Roll in pecans until completely covered.
Place on foil lined tray.
Chill until firm.
Place in paper bonbon cups.
Store in airtight container.
May also coat with coconut or candy sprinkles.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Wrap each piece of chicken in chipped beef. Then wrap with Swiss cheese. Hold together with toothpicks. Mix together sour cream and mushroom soup. Pour over chicken that has been placed in a baking dish. Let marinate overnight. Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine first four ingredients in top of double boiler and beat until thoroughly mixed.
Place over rapidly boiling water until it stands in peaks or 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: chocolate frosties
directions: Pour into Ice cream freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook ingredients over low heat until apples are slightly tender.
Pour ingredients into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Cut another 9-inch pie crust into strips and place on top of apples. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut lard into flour with two butter knives, or pastry utensil.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over flour slowly while mixing with a fork.
Mix together until all is moistened.
Make into 2 or 3 balls (depending on how thick you like your crust)
Handle as little as possible and use a minimum of flour when rolling out.
Bake at 425 degree for pre-baked crust.
Makes 2 or 3 pie crusts or 2 crusts and lattice top for one pie.

title: chicken crepes
directions: Spread rolls out flat.
Place chicken on large end of roll and roll up.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Place rolls in dish so they do not touch.
Add undiluted soup.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Follow directions on box for cake.
Blend together the butter, cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Add pineapple and coconut; blend together.
Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Slice the 2 cake layers in half to make 4 layers.
Put filling between cake layers.
Good holiday cake.

title: crabmeat bisque
directions: Mix soups in a large saucepan, gradually adding the milk.
Stir until well blended.
Stir Imo to soften.
Reserving 6 teaspoons of Imo for topping, add sherry and Imo to soup mixture.
Mix well and add shredded crabmeat.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Pour onto graham cracker crumbs. Press in pan. Freeze until firm.

title: baked chicken and rice - one pan
directions: Mix rice, onion, soups and water together.
Pour into deep baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and place on top of rice - mix. Place chicken on top of rice and bake for 2 1/2 hours at 350 degrees.
Cover with foil.
Baste chicken periodically with more oleo until done.

title: hippopotamus chowder
directions: Cut hippo into bite size pieces.
This usually takes 3 to 4 minutes.
Using a kerosene burner and a very large vat, begin simmering meat, water, salt and pepper.
This recipe should feed about 2,500 people.
If more are expected, the rabbits may be added.
However, try to avoid doing so, as most people do not like hare in their chowder.

title: cornbread(for heart patients)
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a thin batter.
Spray pan with Pam and bake in preheated oven at 500° until brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: May add chocolate chips, coconut, nuts or raisins.

title: frangelico cheesecake
directions: Blend in 3 cups sour cream.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 375° until set and color is light tan (40 to 45 minutes).
Cool at room temperature, then store in fridge for 4 or 5 hours.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at
350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate praline peanuts
directions: Combine brown sugar, water, and peanuts in a large saucepan. Cook over medium to medium high heat until water evaporates and peanuts become sugar coated. Remove from heat.
Remove peanuts and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 375 for about 10 to 12 minutes. Cool completely.
Melt the coating chocolate (can be done in the microwave). Coat the peanuts with the chocolate and place on cookie sheet to cool completely.
Be sure to separate the peanuts before coating has set.

title: mexican fondue
directions: Cut cheese into chunks and melt in a double boiler.
Add diced green chilies and salsa.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Serve warm with French bread chunks and/or veggies.

title: french market soup
directions: Wash beans and put in heavy pot, cover with water and soak overnight.
Drain.
Add 3 quarts of water, ham bone, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered for 2 1/2 hours.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove ham bone, cut meat from bone, chop meat and return to soup pot.
You can add a bag of Bouquet Garni, pieces of steamed smoked sausage or 1/2 c. red wine or all three!
This soup improves with age!

title: layered jello salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; reserve juice.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add the cold water.
Place 1/2 can of fruit in bottom of 8-inch square pan or an angel food pan.
Cover with half of the jello.
Chill until firm.

title: baptist punch
directions: Heat sugar and water, then cool.
Mix Jell-O as directed in water and cool.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add pineapple juice, lemonade and almond extract.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons. Flavors of Jell-O can vary according to the color you want.

title: cocktail sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix meat mixture and form into small balls.
Brown at 375° for 30 minutes in oven; drain.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Cook zucchini until clear; do not let burn.
Add lemon juice, sugar and pineapple.
Bring to a hard boil and boil for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O. Heat to boiling point.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Yields 4 pints.

title: yummy broccoli and rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Cook broccoli slightly and drain.
Combine broccoli, celery, onion and rice.
Blend soup, milk and Cheez Whiz and add to broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain juice from one jar of artichokes into a skillet.
Saute onion and garlic in juice.
Drain other jar and chop all artichokes.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add bread crumbs, Tabasco sauce, oregano, salt and pepper.
Stir in onion, garlic, cheese and artichokes.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut in squares and serve hot.
Can be made in advance and rewarmed on a cookie sheet.
Yields 30 squares.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Gradually whisk in water until smooth.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Gradually whisk 1 cup hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Return to heat.
Add lemon juice and peel. Boil 1 minute.
Add butter.
Cover with plastic wrap.

title: head cheese
directions: Soak head in salt water about 1 hour; wash.
Cook about 3 hours or until meat falls off bone.
Mix all ingredients.
Spread out in 9-inch square dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Make sure the meat is cooked well done.

title: soft peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together until thoroughly blended.
Shape into balls about the size of hickory nuts.
Place in refrigerator and let cool for an hour.
Melt 1 package chocolate chips and about 1/2 cake paraffin over boiling water.
Dip peanut butter balls in melted chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Hold peanut balls with toothpick to dip.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread out with fingers in pan as thin as you can.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: black bean soup
directions: Cook beans until tender with 8 cups water, cajun seasonings, salt and pepper to taste, chopped onion and Italian sausages. Serve topped with sour cream and freshly chopped green onions.

title: white mandarin cake
directions: Blend together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in three 9-inch cake pans.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix and mold into a long roll.
Let stand in refrigerator to stiffen.
Slice very thin and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes (until golden brown).

title: gooy globby bars
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and pour into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: burrito bake
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add 1/4 cup of water to taco seasoning mix.
Blend well and add to ground beef.
Mix together the refried beans, Bisquick and 1/4 cup water.
Spread in well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then layer the seasoned meat and chunky salsa.
On top, sprinkle Cheddar cheese and salsa, if any left.
You may layer Cheddar cheese with meat and salsa. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Let sit a few minutes before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix everything but 1/2 can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining fried onions and bake for 5 more minutes.

title: smoky ham casserole
directions: Microwave potatoes on High 2 minutes on each side.
Cool, peel and dice small.
Combine all ingredients except save half of the onions.
Pour into Pam sprayed 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake uncovered 2 to 5 minutes longer or until light brown.

title: 1, 2, 3, 4 cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add dry ingredients and milk to egg mixture, alternating dry ingredients and milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: apple cobbler
directions: *Melt margarine in 10 x 14 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: rob's french fried onions
directions: Remove skin from onions and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Cover with cold water.
Let stand 30 minutes.	Wipe dry.
Separate into rings.
Combine egg with milk.
Add dry ingredients.
Add oil and mix thoroughly.
Add onions to batter.
Deep-fry until brown.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put milk, potatoes, clam chowder and margarine in pot.
Let it come to a boil, then add oysters.
Turn stove off.
It's ready!

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure flour into bowl.
Make a well in center and add egg yolks, whole egg and salt.
With hands, thoroughly mix egg into flour. Add water, one teaspoon at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
(Add only enough water to form dough into a ball.) Flatten and cut into strips.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together and let come to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer.
The longer it simmers, the better it tastes.
You can also use a crock-pot for this.

title: irish sherry trifle
directions: Prepare custard sauce.
Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup of milk and set aside.
Beat together sugar, egg yolk and water. Set aside.
In the top of a double boiler, scald remaining milk and very slowly add cornstarch mixture, stirring constantly.

title: party punch(serves 35)
directions: Combine orange juice, water and sugar slowly with mixer.
Very slowly, add milk.
Freeze in containers.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Good neutral color.

title: egg nog
directions: In small punch bowl or pitcher, combine sweetened condensed milk and water.
Set aside.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to very soft peaks; stir into sweetened condensed milk mixture. Chill.
Garnish with nutmeg.
Refrigerate any leftovers.
(May be served hot, but do not boil.)

title: onion mushroom sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter in a large skillet.
Add gravy mix, water, wine and pepper; bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Add mushrooms and green onion; cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve hot with beef patties or steak.

title: card party casserole
directions: Mix soups together (don't add water).
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer chestnuts and noodles over mix.
Add pepper.
Cover with croutons. Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.
Serves 6.

title: oatmeal cookies(no bake)
directions: Boil together for 1 minute the first 4 ingredients.
Take off stove and add the last 4 ingredients.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: strawberry torte delight
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy; add cream of tarter.
Gradually add sugar; beat stiff.
Fold in crackers, nuts and vanilla. Spread in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Completely cool.

title: pickled sweet peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove core and seeds.
Slice in 1/4-inch strips.
In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, water, 1/2 teaspoon from crisping packet and pickling salt.
Bring to boil.
Add sliced peppers; return to boil.

title: spinach-cheese pie (6)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into partially-cooked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes, until center is set.
Serve hot or cold.

title: linguine with lemon-parsley clam sauce
directions: Drain clam juice from clams; reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter in a saucepan until tender, but not brown, about 3 minutes.
Add reserved clam juice, oregano, salt and pepper; bring to boiling over high heat.
Cook until mixture is reduced to 1 cup, about 5 minutes.
Cook linguine following label directions; drain.
Keep hot in heated serving bowl.
Lower heat under clam juice mixture; add reserved clams, parsley, lemon rind and lemon juice; heat thoroughly.
Pour over hot linguine and toss.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix and form into balls. Heat at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: striped delight
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup of sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: jeanne's salmon salad(servings:  4)
directions: Drain and remove skin and bones from salmon.
Flake.
Mix all ingredients and add dressing and serve on lettuce with canned potato sticks on top for crunch.

title: brandy slush
directions: Heat water and sugar to dissolve.
Mix with tea steeped in 12 ounces water, lemonade and orange juice and let cool.
Add brandy and freeze.
Mix often.
Mix a scoop of the frozen mixture with either sweet or sour soda, to taste.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook peas in sweet water (1 tablespoon sugar).
Flake tuna and toss lightly with peas and mushroom soup.
Place in casserole. Top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: madge's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and milk. Beat egg into mixture. Combine flour, salt, baking soda (sifted). Mix in chocolate chips. Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Chop all vegetables into bite sized pieces.
Add vegetables, drained olives, cubed cheese and salad seasoning to pasta.
Add Italian dressing and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.
Toss prior to serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and chill.
Cut tomatoes and cucumbers into small cubes; add onion, diced.
Mix well with salad dressing; add Salad Supreme.
Fold this mixture into chilled spaghetti.

title: good chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, water, pudding mix, eggs, oil and sour cream.
Add chocolate chips and pecans; pour into tube pan.
Bake in a 300° to 325° oven for approximately 1 hour.
Cool and glaze with a mixture of confectioners sugar, cocoa and milk.

title: sweet-sour red cabbage
directions: Fry bacon in 12-inch skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, crumble and reserve.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons bacon fat. Stir brown sugar, flour, salt and pepper into bacon fat until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and refrigerate no longer than 48 hours.
Heat over medium heat, stirring occasionally until hot, about 15 minutes.

title: mexican vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and chill at least one hour. Serve with tortilla chips. Easy and wonderful!

title: amaretto coffee creamer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well to blend.
Store in an airtight container.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine crab meat, pepper and onion.
Gently fold in mayonnaise.
Mold the mixture into clean crab shells or other heatproof serving dish.
Cover with melted butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown and mixture is hot.

title: tom's "rebel yell" road kill chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Pour off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients and simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally or until mixture becomes thick.
Serve with plenty of cold beer and saltines.

title: zucchini cake
directions: In a bowl, beat the eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla.
Beat until lemon colored.
Peel and remove seeds from zucchini squash and grate coarsely.
Add to mixture with flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar when cool.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; add other ingredients.
Stir.
Pour in Pyrex dish and chill until firm.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Melt yeast in warm water. Melt butter and set aside.
Add to dry ingredients.
Spoon in muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sour milk spice cake(mother's)
directions: Mix in order given.

title: cajun shrimp
directions: Bring water and lemon to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turn pink.
Drain well; rinse with cold water. Chill. Peel and de-vein shrimp.
Place shrimp in a large heavy-duty, zip-top plastic bag.
Combine vegetable oil and remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over shrimp.
Seal bag; marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours.
Drain before serving.

title: vanilla butternut cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease 10-inch tube pan and dust with flour.

title: lo-cal chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Cream butter, add syrup, salt, and vanilla;
blend.
Stir in cocoa.
Add milk and sugar alternately, beating until smooth and creamy after each addition.
Add enough milk to make a good spreading consistency.
Yield: 2 1/3 cups.
Will frost, fill, and border 1 (10 inch) round, 2 layer cake.

title: no hassle jambalaya
directions: Melt margarine.
Add 1 cup chopped mixture.
Add meat and cook a few minutes until changes color and meat seals.
Add onion soup and simmer (do not dilute soup).
Wash 1 cup rice and drain.
Add rice to meat and 2 cups of water.
Simmer to boil on medium heat. Lower heat and cover.
Stir occasionally until rice is cooked.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Mix ingredients in skillet and serve.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix pancake mix, sugar and milk. Pour evenly over butter. Spoon sliced peaches in lines over pancake mix. (With canned peaches, reserve most of the juice to be used after the cobbler has baked.) Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, depending on your oven. Serve with or without added juice.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend for 30 seconds. Chill overnight.
Serve with pieces of fresh fruit.

title: mom's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time, sour cream and flavoring, then flour and soda which have been sifted together.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in oven which has been preheated to 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: ripe tomato ketchup
directions: Cook all ingredients until thick; put in cans while hot.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In casserole
layer cooked noodles, corned beef, cheese and onion.
Mix
together
soup
with milk.
Pour over layers. Top with crushed chips.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: seafood batter
directions: Combine ingredients and dip seasoned shrimp or any seafood in batter.
Fry until golden brown.

title: special k candy
directions: Bring Karo and sugar to a boil.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Pour mixture over cereal and mix until well coated.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with water.
Lastly, stir in kraut.

Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or use two 8-inch square pans. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in the square pans, longer in the 9 x 13-inch pan. Check for doneness. When cool, ice with chocolate icing.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in a large Dutch oven, stirring to crumble; drain off pan drippings.
Add celery, cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add next 8 ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Add green pepper, cover and cook 10 minutes.
Makes about 16 cups.

title: cool whip supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl and chill.

title: impossible brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate.
Beat all ingredients, except nuts, until smooth for 2 minutes in blender on high.
Pour into pie plate, sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water until tender.
Place saucepan under cold running water and let noodles stand in cool water to prevent sticking together.
Brown meat with onions; add sauce and set aside.
Combine eggs, Ricotta and parsley.
Line a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish or lasagne pan with one layer of noodles. Layer with sauce, Ricotta mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan. Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This freezes well before and after baking.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, put a layer of tuna, a layer of chips and cream of mushroom soup.
Repeat layers.
Cook until soupy, about 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, salt, pineapple, onions, peppers and 2/3 cup nuts.
Roll into ball and roll into remaining nuts. Refrigerate and serve with Ritz crackers.

title: turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey and celery in bowl.
Mix salad dressing (or mayonnaise), salt, poultry seasoning, onion salt, and pepper. Pour over turkey and celery.
Toss.
Serves 3 - 4.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In a pan, melt butter. Add onion, green pepper and salt; saute. Mix corn, eggs, muffin mix and 1 cup of cheese. Add the sauteed onions and peppers. Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop the popcorn dry, no butter or oil.
Put in a big roaster or pan (not plastic).
In saucepan, mix white sugar and butter until you can spin a thread on medium heat.
Then remove and add soda, then add milk.
Beat until foamy.
Pour over popcorn and mix.
Put butter on hands and make balls.
Wrap in paper (wax or plastic wrap) and you are done and they are good.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir once.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours or high 5 to 6 hours.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare
cake mix according to directions.
Pour batter into a greased
x
15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan.

title: chicken souffle
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Line bottom with 8 slices of bread.
Cover with sliced chicken meat; spread slices with mayonnaise and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese.
Top with remaining 8 slices bread.
Beat together eggs, milk and salt and pour over entire casserole.
Refrigerate overnight, or all day. When ready to bake, pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese; return to oven and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Serves 10.
Can be multiplied.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix all ingredients together except crackers.
Pour over crackers.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar with a wire whisk. Gently stir in cool whip. Add remaining ingredients and whisk until well blended. Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Bake in 3 layers at 350° (may use tube or loaf pan).
Cook about 45 minutes.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill if necessary.
Form into balls and roll in granulated sugar.
(I prefer medium-size cookies and scoop up 1 tablespoon of dough for each ball.)
Place on cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes.
Cookies will flatten and crinkle. Delicious!

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into a large casserole dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Pour melted butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat, be sure to crumble it.
Drain well.
Warm up the sauce.
Dip tortillas in the sauce and line the bottom of the pan with tortillas.
Cover tortillas with meat and cheese and repeat with second layer and so on.
Pour any sauce that's left over it.
Then cover it with more cheese.
Place in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Make a day ahead.
Toast sesame seed and slivered almonds in broiler.
(Watch as they burn easily!)
Put the first six ingredients in large bowl and toss.

title: crawfish jambalaya
directions: Saute in butter, sausage, pepper, celery, onions and garlic in iron pot.
Cook until tender but not brown.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Stir once or twice and cover. Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook about 20 minutes or rice is tender. Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.

Stir in melted chocolate. Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Mix at low speed just until blended after each addition.
Add pecans and flavorings.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.

Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 to 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Shield cake with aluminum foil for the last 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely on wire rack.
Yield:
One 10-inch cake.

title: quick pizza bread
directions: Divide the ingredients on each slice of bread.
Bake in oven until browned on top.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve sugar in 1 cup boiling water.
Add instant coffee and let cool.
Add vodka, 1 cup water and vanilla.
Makes 1 quart Kahlua.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry onions (cut up) and celery (cut up) until golden.
Mix together tomato soup, mustard and brown sugar.
Put beans, sausage, onion and celery in large roaster and mix.
Add tomato soup mixture.
Top with tomato paste mixed with water (do not mix with beans).
Can put bacon strips on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 375° or can mix all ingredients together and put in crock-pot.

title: deep-fried phoenix-tailed shrimp
directions: Peel each shrimp shell down to the last section, leaving it and the tail attached to the shrimp.
Cut down the back of each shrimp with a small, sharp knife and remove the black or white intestinal vein.
Wash the shrimp under cold running water and pat them dry with paper towels.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Cook sugar and buttermilk slowly until it forms a soft-ball stage (I use a candy thermometer). Remove from the stove; add vanilla and nuts. Stir until it gets sugary. Turn out on wax paper-lined cookie sheet. Pull apart while still warm. Let dry completely.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and 2 cups of the sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix soda to sour cream, then add to butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Mix thoroughly, then add flour.
Beat egg whites umtil they hold a peak.
Beat in the additional cup of sugar, then fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Use a large tube pan.

title: overnight broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli in pieces.
Add crumbled bacon and cheese.
Mix mayo with sugar and vinegar and frost the broccoli.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Stir well and serve.

title: pecan bars
directions: Mix butter, flour and sugar like pie crust.
Pat on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Mix brown sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Fold in pecans.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: lynne's popular pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Gradually add flour and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: baklava
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 300 degrees F. Spray a 9 x 13 inch pan with non-stick cooking spray.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all but last 2 ingredients and fold into potatoes.
Add last 1/2 stick butter to cornflakes and sprinkle on top of potato mixture which is placed in a 13 x 9-inch pan before topping.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Test potatoes for doneness.

title: rotel sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Melt cheese and add sausage and tomatoes.
Reheat until all ingredients are to your desired temperature.
Serve with your favorite chips or crackers.

title: date macaroon pie
directions: In small mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar. Gradually add milk, beating until mixture is smooth.
Stir in macaroon crumbs, dates and pecans.
Beat cream just to soft peaks. Fold whipped cream into cheese mixture.
Turn into pie shell. Chill until firm.
Garnish with orange.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain and squeeze spinach in paper towel.
Put all ingredients in food processor and blend.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve in cored out cabbage with favorite crackers.

title: italian bountiful harvest(low fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 10-inch deep dish pie plate or quiche dish with butter-flavored cooking spray.
Evenly layer zucchini, onion and tomato into prepared pie plate.
Sprinkle Parmesan and cheddar cheeses evenly over vegetables.
In a medium bowl, combine evaporated skim milk, biscuit baking mix, black pepper and parsley flakes.
Mix well using a wire whisk.
Pour mixture evenly over top.
Bake for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Place pie plate on a wire rack and let set for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Peel and dice.
Add vinegar and seasonings.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook eggs 4 minutes. Combine potatoes, bacon, 4 tablespoons bacon fat, soft-cooked eggs and onions.
Keep warm until served.

title: mary's mississippi mud brownies
directions: Melt sugar and butter together until creamy.
Beat in eggs, flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend in cocoa, vanilla and walnuts and combine thoroughly.
Spread batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownies test done.
Remove from oven and while brownies are hot, cover with marshmallows.
Cover pan with foil and let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until marshmallows melt evenly over brownies; let cool on rack.
Meanwhile, prepare icing.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce, garlic salt and chili powder.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer.
Alternate layers of Fritos, hamburger, cheese, chiles and end with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until cheese is completely melted on top.
Serves 4.

title: green rice
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook rice.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Mix rice, Cheez Whiz, broccoli and celery.
Place in casserole and pour soup over.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Boil 1 pound of Mueller's elbow macaroni, drain and set aside. Melt butter in a pot over low flame.
Slowly add flour and salt and blend.
Stir constantly with milk added, and cook slowly over low heat until sauce thickens a little.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Mix with macaroni.
Place in a large baking dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: tea time cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars, add egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and blend with shortening mixture.
Add oats, Wheaties, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.	Drop by small spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 for 15 minutes. Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: ontbyt koek(breakfast cake)
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl.
Pour in honey and milk.
Mix with mixer on low setting just until mixed.
Butter baking loaf pan and dust with flour.
Preheat oven on 325°.
Bake for approximately 1 hour (or until toothpick comes out clean).
Serve plain for breakfast with tea or coffee as snack or dessert.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together like meat loaf.
Roll in 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Place on wire rack.
Poke holes in foil.
This is very important so the grease can get out.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can freeze.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift together flour, soda and salt and add to mixture along with nuts, chips and cherries.
Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil together for
minutes
sugar, orange rind and 5 cups water.
Strain and cool.
Place tea bags in an enamel pot and pour over
them	8
cups
freshly
boiling water.
Steep 3 minutes. Strain.
Mix
the tea, syrup and fruit juices.
Keep hot until ready to serve.
Do not boil.
Yield:
25 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Salt and paprika the chicken the night before, so that it will stand several hours.
In a casserole place bacon.
Pour rice over the bacon.
Place the chicken on the rice, pour cream of chicken soup over the chicken and rice.
Then add water and pour same over the chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
If you desire to have the chicken a light brown, remove the foil the last 10 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute peppers and onions in oil over high heat for 4 minutes. Stir in 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Combine 1/3 cup soy sauce and lime juice; pour over chicken in a large plastic bag.
Marinate for 1 hour.
Reserve marinade.

title: greek-style lamb burritos
directions: Crumble lamb into 10 to 12-inch frying pan over medium heat, stirring often, until meat is well browned.
With a slotted spoon, transfer lamb from pan.
Discard drippings and wipe pan clean with paper towel.
To pan, add broth, onion, garlic and bell pepper. Stir occasionally on high heat until pan is almost dry, then stir often until dark brown bits stick in pan.
Stir bits free with 2 to 3 tablespoons water.
Repeat until brown bits form, then deglaze pan again with 2 to 3 tablespoons water.
Repeat this step until onions have a deep, rich brown color, about 15 minutes total.
Return lamb to pan along with tomato sauce, 1 cup water, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, lemon juice, parsley and hot pepper seasoning.
Stir to free browned bits.
Bring to boil over high heat, then reduce heat and simmer uncovered until mixture is reduced to about 3 cups, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix well and add crab meat.
Bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top and serve with crackers when melted.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan well.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan. Space rolls evenly on top of nuts.
Mix pudding mix, sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top of rolls.
Melt butter; pour over rolls. Let set overnight.
The rolls will rise and fill the pan.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Make glaze.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Break 1/2 cake in bowl (small pieces).
Add 1/2 pudding over cake.
Put 1/2 Cool Whip over. Crush 1/2 candy over.
Repeat with remaining ingredients in same order.

title: taboli wheat or bulgar
directions: Chop all vegetables fine.
Add the oil, lemon juice and salt. Mix and let set 2 hours.

title: fruit french dressing
directions: Combine all these together (beat with egg beater).

title: citrus warmer
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan and heat until boiling. Transfer to a crock-pot on low to keep warm while serving.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large pan, heat oil.
Add onions and saute over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally, until bouillon cubes are dissolved. Gradually, add noodles and salt so that bouillon mixture continues to boil.
Cook uncovered for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in broccoli and garlic salt and cook 4 minutes more.
Add milk and cheese and continue cooking until cheese melts, stirring constantly.

title: quick sweet sour chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
In small bowl, stir together cornstarch, reserved juice, corn syrup, vinegar, ketchup and soy sauce.
In large skillet or wok, heat corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Re-stir cornstarch mixture; stir into chicken.
Stirring constantly, bring to boil; boil 1 minute.
Stir in pineapple and pepper strips; heat through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add juice, vegetables and spices.
Cook until vegetables are done.

title: great grandmother's soft ginger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
Add the brown sugar and mix well.
Then add the eggs and blend.
Add the ginger to the molasses and mix. Then add to the sugar mixture.
Add the boiling water while stirring.
Sift the remaining ingredients together and add to the sugar mixture.
Mix well and then place in the refrigerator for 2 hours.
Drop by the teaspoonfuls on a greased baking sheet. Sprinkle granulated sugar on the top before baking.
Bake in a hot oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and lightly chop bell peppers.
Mix all ingredients together and cook 1 hour.
At end of cooking time, add tomato paste.
Stir frequently, bring back to boil.
Put in hot jars; seal.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites.
Slowly add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pie plate and spray with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Chill 2 to 8 hours or freeze.
Top with whipped cream.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Stew meat in as little water as possible until half done.
Add rest of ingredients and cook together until done.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover with ice cubes and soak for one hour.
Drain and wash well.

title: raspberry vinaigrette
directions: Combine ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly and shake vigorously.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in vegetable oil at medium heat for 40 minutes. Stir in cornstarch for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.

title: broccoli cornbread casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in 3-quart casserole at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden.
Yummy!!!

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling liquid.
Blend in cranberry sauce, crushed pineapple and chopped nuts.
Spoon into mold and chill until firm.

title: hot watermelon soup
directions: Crush a few garlic cloves and simmer them in some olive oil to flavor it.
Do not burn or overbrown them.
Add stock to this after barely simmering the watermelon white cubes in it.
Add the dried mushrooms and bay leaf and simmer for about 25 minutes to soften the cubes and to rehydrate the mushrooms.
Serve hot with Tabasco sauce as an option for adding as well as cilantro leaves, shredded bacalao and Parmesan cheese.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine Cool Whip, milk and lemon juice.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.

title: quickie stickie buns
directions: In a large bowl, measure 1 1/2 cups flour and 2 packages yeast. In a saucepan, blend milk, water, butter, sugar and salt.
Stirring constantly, heat until warm.
Pour into flour mixture and egg. Beat 1/2 minute at low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand gradually add 1 1/4 cups flour. Scrape from bottom and sides of bowl.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes in warm place.
Make topping.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: In a
small bowl, stir together the sour cream and baking soda; set aside.
Cream butter with sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in sour cream mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients until dry ingredients are just blended.
Do not overmix.
Divide mixture between 3 mini loaf pans (6 x 5 x 2-inch) and bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Allow to cool in pans 15 minutes and then remove from pans and continue cooling on a rack.
Yields 3 mini loaves.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened; do not beat.
Stir in vanilla extract, butter flavor, pineapple, 1 cup of pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into three 9-inch round greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers, on top and sides of cake, then sprinkle the half-cup of chopped pecans on top.
Refrigerate.
Flavors blend and intensify upon standing for 24 hours after baking.
Makes one 3-layer cake.

title: sugar 'n spice nuts
directions: Beat the egg white.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put in nuts and stir until they are coated.
Place in a flat pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour or until golden.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut in quarters.
Cook covered in a small amount of boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain.
Re-cover the pot with potatoes.
Meanwhile, in a small saucepan over low heat, cook garlic in milk until garlic is soft, about 30 minutes.
Add milk-garlic mixture and white pepper to potatoes.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed or mash with a potato masher until smooth.
Makes 4 servings.
Calories 141. Total Fat:

title: pancake cake
directions: Makes a 9 x 13-inch pancake.
Add walnuts or raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add sugar and cinnamon on top of cake for topping before baking.

title: caramel apples
directions: Wash and dry apples.
In a small heavy saucepan ove low heat, melt caramels with water, stirring frequently until mixture is smooth.
Place each apple into bowl, spooning mixture over apple until it is completely coated.
Insert wooden stick into stem end and remove from bowl.
Scrape excess coating from bottom of apple. Place apples in greased waxed paper and chill until set.

title: peanut butter drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream the butter, peanut butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Add cream mixture, stirring until well combined.
Stir in cereal; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Line microwave cupcake pan with paper liners.
In a large bowl, measure water.
Cook on High 2 to 3 minutes until boiling. Add bran cereal.
Stir until cereal is moistened.
Add butter and let mixture stand 5 to 6 minutes until cereal is softened.
With wire whisk, stir in sugar and eggs, beating until well mixed. Blend in flour, baking soda and buttermilk.
Spoon batter into desired number of paper-lined cups, filling half full.
Remaining batter may be stored in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Microwave 2 muffins on High 1 minute, 4 muffins 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or 6 muffins for 2 to 3 minutes.
(Muffins will be flat, they do not peak.)
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 42 muffins, 65 calories each.

title: quesadilla supreme
directions: Brown beef and season according to taco seasoning directions. Butter 1 side of tortilla and place on cookie sheet, butter side down.
Cover with the following layers:
beans, taco beef and two cheeses that have been mixed together.
Cover with another flour tortilla that has been buttered on the top side.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes at 500°.
Broil 1 to 2 minutes or until slightly brown and cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and top with guacamole, black olives, tomatoes, onions and a spoonful of sour cream.
Cut into 4 wedges to serve.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except pineapple juice.
Boil, then add pineapple juice and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: poor man's soup
directions: All cans should be 10 to 14 ounces.

title: italian delight
directions: Saute green pepper, onion and parsley in butter or oleo.
Add beef and cook until brown.
Cook spaghetti in 1 gallon of water with 2 tablespoons salt.
Wash and drain.
Combine all ingredients (2 1/2 tablespoons salt).
Mix and bake in pans in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 50.

title: aunt jody's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese; gradually add sugar, then eggs one at a time.
Gradually add flour, then extract.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great for the holidays.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter or margarine into cake mix until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Press mixture lightly in bottom and one inch up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: kentucky butter cake with butter sauce
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cream butter first, then cream with sugar, adding gradually.
Cream well.
Blend in eggs, beating well after each egg.
Combine buttermilk or sour milk and vanilla.
Add milk mixture alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture, starting and ending with dry ingredients, blending well each addition on low speed.
Grease bottom only of tube pan.
Pour in mixture evenly.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes until cake springs back when touched in center.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs. Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.

title: ooie-gooie
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut into small squares when completely cooled.
This is also good if you add coconut to the cream cheese mixture.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Add Quaker oats. Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: oatmeal coffee cake(sugar free)
directions: Mix and bake at 375° in small baking dish for about 20 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Do not overbake!
Delicious with light cream cheese spread over while warm.
Serves 1.
Counts as 1 bread, 1 milk and 1 fruit.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix together cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion, garlic powder and chopped beef.
Shape into balls or logs and roll in chili powder and pecans.
Wrap in Handi-Wrap and place in fridge until ready to use.
Best if can set overnight.

title: chicken-n-biscuits
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Put cream soup in bottom of cake pan.
Stir in cooked chicken; top with unbaked biscuits until top is covered.
Bake at temperature as directed on biscuits.
Serve when cooled.

title: hot cheese squares
directions: Beat eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Add green chilies and cheeses.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and Doritos in a salad bowl.
Combine hamburger and taco sauce and serve hot over salad mixture.

title: corn relish
directions: Wash and prepare raw vegetables.
Chop into pieces about 1/4 inch in size or in cubes, then measure.
Put in large saucepan and add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Boil 20 minutes.
Add drained corn; cook 5 minutes longer or until corn is thoroughly heated.

title: pink cloud
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan; add gelatin.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Cool to room temperature, then add other ingredients.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: sour cream shrimp
directions: Thaw frozen shrimp with cold water or drain canned shrimp. Cut large shrimp in half. In a frying pan cook mushrooms and onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour. Add soup; cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add sour cream, pepper, and shrimp. Heat. Serve on toast points and serve. Serves 6.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use enough flour to roll.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar and bake in hot oven, 400°.
Before baking, I put in just a small amount of jam or jelly in center; adds something!

title: creamy turkey and pasta
directions: Prepare pasta according to directions.
Add broccoli, carrots and onions during last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
Combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling.
Add pasta and vegetables.
Heat through over low heat.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add undrained pineapple and strawberries.
Stir.
Chill until thick.
Fold in bananas.
Pour half into a lightly oiled baking dish (9 x 11-inch).
Chill until set.
Set aside the remaining Jell-O mixture.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add sour cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Spread on set Jell-O layer.
Chill for at least 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Jell-O.
Chill until set.
Best if made the night before because of the time it takes each layer to set.

title: mama and daddy's meat sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients except last 3 together, then add the tomatoes, paste and sauce.
Thin with 1 can of water.
Cook 2 1/2 to
3 hours.
Add 1 tablespoon of Parmesan cheese.
Cook 30 minutes more.
Serve over spaghetti or other pasta.

title: frozen date salad
directions: Chop dates, cherries and nuts.
Beat cream cheese with mixer. Add pineapple and blend well.
Add dates, cherries and lemon juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Freeze until firm.

title: lo-cal mustard dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in closed container.
Two tablespoons are considered free on most food plans.

title: cheesy broccoli bake
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine the soup and sour cream.
Stir in the broccoli, ham and rice.
Mix well. In a cup, combine bread crumbs and margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, pepper, sugar, and cornstarch and mix. Add corn.
Mix in melted butter.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30- 35 minutes.
Very delicious! Can be made ahead and put in oven just before dinner.

title: crackling corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add the milk and cracklings.
Shape into small, long rolls and place on a baking sheet or pour batter into a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Bake rolls 20 minutes in a 425° oven or bake in square pan in a 450° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: festive cauliflower
directions: In covered skillet, in 1/2 inch boiling water, cook cauliflower 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Drain.
Stir in soup, milk, curry and pepper until smooth.
Add peas and red pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Add cheese last 30 seconds of cooking.
Top with almonds. Makes 5 cups.

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder together 3 times.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Add vanilla.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
Add taco sauce to make desired consistency.

title: lasagna roll-ups
directions: Lay each noodle on flat surface.
Combine Ricotta and egg. Spread thin layer of Ricotta over noodle.
Then apply thin layer of chopped spinach.
Roll up and cut in half.
Using 9 x 13-inch pan, place roll-up curly side up in pan.
Continue this process with remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over roll-ups.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over roll-ups.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: lazy enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and onion; break tortillas in bite size pieces. Add tortillas, sauce and 2 cups cheese to meat.
Place in casserole and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(If not moist enough, add one 8-ounce can tomato sauce.) You may also add chili powder to taste.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix milk, sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar together and pour over chilled vegetables and macaroni. Refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Freeze on a cookie sheet.
Place in freezer-type baggies.
Take out any amount and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 60 to 70 balls.

title: hamburger delish
directions: Mix together and cook at least 30 minutes.
I like just a little hot sauce or a pod of red hot pepper.

title: roasted asparagus
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Snap off the tough ends of asparagus and, if desired, peel the stalks. In a shallow roasting pan or baking sheet with sides, toss asparagus with oil and season with salt and pepper. Spread asparagus in a single layer. Use 2 pans if necessary. Roast for 10-15 minutes until tender and browned, shaking once during roasting. Sprinkle with the vinegar and toss. Taste to adjust seasonings. Serve hot or let cool to room temperature and serve within 2 hours. Serves 10-12. 51 calories, 2 g. fat, 7 g. carbohydrates, 6 mg. sodium.

title: quick "mini" pizzas
directions: Place toasted muffins on baking sheet.
Place 1 tablespoon of pizza sauce on toasted muffin.
Top with shredded cheese of your choice.
Broil until golden brown on top.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onions in butter; add hamburger and brown.
Add oregano, garlic salt, salt, pepper, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce. Mix well.
Add soups; cover and simmer for 5 to 15 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix and pudding mix.
Beat in all other ingredients except for chocolate chips.
Fold in chocolate chips with spatula.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour in greased tube pan.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, onion and pimiento in medium bowl. Measure remaining ingredients into jar; cover with lid and shake to blend well. Pour dressing over vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Refrigerate, covered, at least 2 hours to allow flavors to blend. Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: california blend casserole
directions: Put vegetables in 9 to 12-inch glass dish.
Mix in soup.
Put cheese on top, then melt butter and crushed crackers and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
I like the celery soup.

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Cook together the ground chuck, onion, bell pepper, salt and pepper.
Mix together the soup, cream of corn and tomato sauce. Layer noodles, meat mixture, soup mixture and sprinkle cheese. Repeat.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: color me pudding
directions: For One:
Mix 1 tablespoon instant pudding and 1/4 cup milk in a paper cup.
Add food coloring.

title: stewed potatoes
directions: Cook the first three ingredients together until almost done. Add 1/2 stick margarine.
Beat flour and milk until all lumps are gone. Remove potatoes from heat.
Add flour mixture.
Return to heat.
Cook a few minutes.
Black pepper to taste.

title: slow pot barbecue beef with 7-up
directions: Cut fat from roast; place meat in slow pot.
Mix barbecue sauce and 7-Up; pour over roast.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or until meat can be broken apart.
Serve over kaiser buns.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir pumpkin, milk and egg in until smooth.
