Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Mix remaining ingredients and sprinkle on top.
Place pan on shallow baking sheet and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine, marshmallows and chocolate in saucepan. Remove from heat.
Add cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: chocolate peanut buddy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth, about 1 minute.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in 1 cup morsels.

title: mud bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a bowl, beat brown sugar, butter and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg; beat well.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate morsels and all nuts. Spread in foil-lined 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 23 to 25 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate morsels over top.
When morsels are shiny, spread evenly with a knife.
When cool, chill 10 minutes to set chocolate.
Cut into 2 x 1 1/2-inch bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: amish cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients together and blend well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: roasted fries with honey mustard sauce
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise into 4 wedges, then cut each wedge into 5/8-inch strips.

title: chicken-ham salad in tomatoes
directions: Combine chicken, ham, onion and French dressing; cover and chill at least 1 hour. Mix mayonnaise and mustard; add with celery to salad. Toss lightly. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Place tomatoes, stem end down, and cut each, not quite through in 6 wedges. Spread tomato wedges apart; sprinkle with salt and fill with salad. Top with parsley or ripe olives. Serve on lettuce.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into small balls.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: orange wheat germ muffins
directions: Combine wheat germ, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and orange peel.
Beat together oil, egg and orange juice.
Add all at once to dry ingredients and stir just to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with wheat germ topping.
Press in lightly.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: chilies rellenos casserole
directions: Arrange chilies on bottom of cake pan.
Mix cheese and spread on top.
Mix milk and eggs and pour over cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Take out and pour tomato sauce over it. Return to oven for 12 minutes. Serves 6 heartily.

title: microwave taco casserole
directions: Place ground beef in 1 1/2-quart microwave casserole. Microwave for 4 to 5 minutes or until beef loses its color, stirring after 2 minutes.
Pour off drippings.
Add next 3 ingredients, mixing well.
Microwave for 3
minutes, bringing mixture to a boil.
Spread corn chips in microwave pie plate. Press refried beans on top, forming a shell.
Fill with ground beef mixture.
Microwave for 3 minutes or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Microwave 1 minute.
Serve with taco sauce, if desired. Yields 6 servings, about 454 calories each.

title: swiss fudge
directions: Melt chocolates in microwave oven.
Do not cook.
After chocolate is melted, pour the warm cream in slowly.
Stir well with electric mixer.
Add walnuts, if used.
Pour in 9 x 9-inch pan coated with butter.
Cool for 2 hours before cutting.
Delicious!

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let cool.
Mix all together. Grease and flour 5 tin cans; fill half full.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool, slice and serve with whipped topping.
Freeze and serve later, also.

title: swiss nut torte
directions: Beat butter until fluffy.
Mix	flour, 1/2 cup of sugar and salt.
Add to
butter.
Beat
until crumbly.
Combine egg, rum and lemon peel.
Stir
into flour mixture until moistened. Divide dough into thirds.	Pat
1/3 into a 10-inch spring-form pan, 1/3 on sides, 1-inch high.
On wax paper, roll last third into a rectangle, 1/4-inch
thick.
Cover	and chill the crust and rectangular dough for 30 minutes.

title: infallable pound cake
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cherry caramel ring(coffee cake)
directions: Place butter in 8-inch round dish.
Microwave at High (10) for 1 minute until melted.
Sprinkle sugar over butter and add corn syrup.
Stir well with fork.
Place glass open side up in center of dish.
Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Arrange biscuits over mixture in dish in petal shape; squeeze to fit, if necessary. Microwave at Medium (5) for
6 to 8 minutes.
Remove glass and invert onto serving plate.
Let dish stand over rolls a few minutes so remaining syrup in dish may drizzle over rolls.
Serve warm.

title: banana split pie
directions: Layer the graham crackers, pudding, fruit (mixed), graham crackers, pudding and fruit (mixed).
Continue layering until you have used all ingredients.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese, broccoli dip
directions: Chop, cook and drain broccoli.
Chop celery.
Chop onions. Cook rice.
Combine broccoli, celery, onions and rice.
Add mushroom soup and cheese.
Mix well.
Serve hot.
Can be made ahead of time.
Can be frozen.

title: white christmas cookies
directions: Why I like (or memories of) my grandma or grandpa's recipe: Because she makes them every year for Christmas.

title: 7-up bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a 400° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wedding cookies
directions: Mix margarine and 1/2 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and flour, beat until well mixed.
Stir in nuts.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool on pan 2 to 3 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Continue to cool, then roll in sugar again. Store in tin.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a greased 8 x 9 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: watermelon slush
directions: In a large saucepan, combine water and sugar.
Bring to boiling, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil gently, uncovered, for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in frozen fruit punch, until dissolved.

title: apple bundles
directions: Roll sliced apples in dinner rolls.
Pour juice and sugar and cinnamon mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 16 guests.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix together in blender or food processor until oil disappears.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 dry ingredients and add milk.
Stir well; set aside.
Melt 1 stick margarine in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven. Remove from oven when melted.
Pour batter mixture over melted margarine.
Then pour fruit over top of batter (peaches are excellent).
Sprinkle 1/2 cup water and 1/2 cup sugar over fruit. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until batter is done. Cinnamon sprinkled over fruit adds flavor.

title: brussels sprouts pickles
directions: Trim off the hard end of the sprouts. Cut an X in the stem end. Place in a pan of boiling water and cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Drain. Mix together the rest of the ingredients and pour over the hot sprouts. Marinate for 3 to 5 days. Drain and serve.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat all ingredients except popcorn to simmering over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in popcorn.
Cook, stirring constantly, until popcorn is well coated, about 3 minutes; cool slightly.

title: after church stew
directions: Place beef (no need to brown) in 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with celery, onions and carrots. Combine soup and water.
Pour over meat.
Cover tightly and bake in slow oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes and bake 45 minutes longer.
Makes 5 servings.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Cool.
Beat until creamy.
Add pecans, if desired.
Pour onto buttered platter and cut into squares when cold.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice in bowl.
Stir in dry pudding mix; stir until well mixed.
Fold in thawed whipped topping, nuts, marshmallows and cherries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Add sugar, milk, cocoa and syrup. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal and mix well.
Drop tablespoons of mixture onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: chocolate cherries
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and syrup; cut cherries in half or use whole.
Make creamed mixture into walnut sized portions (smaller if desired).
Make a thumbprint hole in each and place cherry inside, then work into a ball and chill overnight.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Fry or microwave bacon until crisp; cool and crumble into large bowl.
Add shredded cheese.
Stir together all remaining ingredients; add to bacon and cheese.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then reduce heat to 350° for another 30 minutes.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: swedish apple bake
directions: Combine the butter and zwieback crumbs.
Butter an ovenproof baking dish.
Pack a layer of crumbs on the bottom.
Cover with a thin layer of applesauce.
Continue to alternate layers of zwieback with applesauce, finally ending with the crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve spooned out with whipped cream.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Wash, hull and mash 2 quarts of strawberries. Add sugar; let stand 1 hour.
Strain.
Add juice of orange and lemons, cold water and sugar.
Pour into large punch bowl.
Add 1 quart of whole strawberries.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: mexican corn salad
directions: Cook corn; drain well.
Pour into serving dish and toss in remaining ingredients.

title: low-fat chicken divan
directions: Cook, bone and chop chicken.
In lightly oiled or Pam sprayed 13x9 dish, layer cooked broccoli, chicken then sauce.
Top with cracker or bread crumbs to cover (I use whole wheat bread), parmesan cheese, and dot with light margarine or oil.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Beat egg and sweetener together; add butter and blend well.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and all spices.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes at 375°.

title: mistake-proof rice(oven rice)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, remove cover and let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy hash browns
directions: Mix well by hand in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Coat chicken in mixture in bag.
Melt shortening or margarine in 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Bake skin side down 30 minutes.
Turn; bake 35 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted margarine together.
Pour out into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly combine the pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Blend in eggs, milk and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell (have edges crimped high; filling is generous).
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake another 40 minutes, or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Cool.

title: memi's tex-mex enchiladas
directions: Brown ground
meat; drain.
Add chili mix, tomato sauce and water.
Mix
flour	with
a little water and add to sauce. Add chili powder and garlic.
Simmer at least 20 minutes.
Add more water if too thick.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cup sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Stir into first mixture.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Mix together 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll balls in the sugar mixture and place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: key lime pie
directions: Blend condensed milk, juice and rind.
Add egg yolks and mix well.
Pour into a baked pie crust.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Add onions and garlic powder. Cook for 5 minutes.
Add pepper, parsley flakes, canned tomatoes, tomato paste, water and seasonings.
Heat to boiling, uncovered. Remove from heat.
Assemble ingredients as follows:

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add soups, Milnot and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: baked fish chowder
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange clean fish in bottom of deep casserole.
Add potatoes, vegetables and seasonings.
Pour wine over top.
Cut butter into bits and scatter on top.
Pour boiling water over all and cover tightly.
Bake 1 hour.
Add warm cream and stir gently.
Serve from casserole.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: In a large serving dish, mix together shredded carrots, apple, pecans, raisins and mayonnaise.

title: feather fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in chocolate squares melted and cooled.
Sift together 2 1/2 cups cake flour. Add baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with cold water, beating after each addition.
Bake in two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans, lightly greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
You can use 2 to 3 envelopes Nestle Choco Bake instead of chocolate squares, also Hershey's cocoa powdered can be used; just follow package directions.
Substitute cake flour for regular, 1 cup minus 2 tablespoons equals 1 cup cake flour.

title: notre dame cookies
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly, except decorations.
Roll dough into 1 inch balls, dip and roll in decorations.
Cover completely. Flatten with glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges turn golden brown.

title: macaroni cups
directions: Cut tops off peppers; remove and discard seeds and cook in boiling salted water for about 5 minutes. Drain and stand in muffin pan cups.

title: caesar salad
directions: Put first six ingredients in a blender and puree.
Slowly add olive oil.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Put lettuce, croutons and cheese in bowl; pour dressing over and toss.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Mix all ingredients well with mixer.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding nuts, zucchini and coconut last.
Bake at 350° in a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes with apples or pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease pan with 1 teaspoon of margarine.
Lay sweet potato and apple slices in pan, alternating and overlapping slices.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over potatoes and apples.
Dot with remaining margarine.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.
Serves 4.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together until potatoes are coated. Put in greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Scald milk and pour over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Mix crumbs and butter.
Remove foil and sprinkle potatoes with crumb mixture. Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water as box states.
Add cream cheese and mash with fork until cheese mostly dissolves.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Sets up in approximately 2 hours.

title: baked zucchini
directions: Mix all together and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and heat about 5 minutes.
Great on chicken or pork.

title: chinese chews
directions: Slowly melt Crisco and butter.
In mixing bowl, add sugar to melted Crisco and butter.
Beat 1 minute.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat 1 minute.
Add flour.
Mix by hand, not mixer.
Add dates and nuts.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt and sift into large bowl.
Add raisins and walnuts to the sifted dry ingredients. Combine beaten egg, vanilla and melted shortening and add to the flour mixture.
Dissolve soda in the undrained crushed pineapple and add to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Pour the batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool bread on a wire rack.
Slice and serve. Spread with butter, oleo or cream cheese.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: veggie squares
directions: Press crescent rolls in a baking pan; press edges together. Bake as on crescent roll can.
Cool.
Spread Ranch dip; spread broccoli, carrots, green onions and cheese on top.
Cut into squares.

title: spiced french toast
directions: In a shallow dish blend eggs, milk, cinnamon, vanilla, salt and nutmeg.
In large skillet melt 2 tablespoons butter flavored Crisco.
Dip both sides of bread in egg mixture.
Place 2 or 3 coated slices in skillet.
Cook over medium heat until deep golden brown on both sides.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Grease or spray 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour mixture into pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: party cheese treat
directions: Beat cream cheese and Cheddar cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: easy baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove bacon. Drain off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in pan.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until onion is tender.
Crumble bacon. Stir bacon, pork and beans, molasses and mustard in saucepan with onion.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients well; cook slowly for 1 hour (keep stirring).
Add 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch, mixed with enough water to pour.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: "trash"(candy)
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate in microwave.
Mix Rice Chex and sugar.
Pour chocolate mixture over Rice Chex and sugar; gently fold until coated.
Pour 1/2 box of powdered sugar into trash bag; add Chex mixture.
Pour other 1/2 box of sugar on top.
Shake and toss gently until coated.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add enough milk to moisten to make a thick batter. Spoon out into balls into a deep fryer.
Take out when golden brown.

title: corny broccoli bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions.
Drain grease.
Combine soup and drained beans in a glass casserole dish.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gold coast pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops and pour off fat.
Stir in soup, 1/2 cup water, carrots and onions.
Cover and let simmer for 15 minutes. Serves 4.

title: deerfield chili
directions: Taste as you go!

title: tamale pie
directions: To half of the shortening, add corn and tomatoes.
Heat slowly.
To remaining shortening, add onion, garlic and green pepper; do not brown.
To this, add meat and chili sauce.
Cook slowly 20 minutes.
Add cornmeal to tomatoes and corn mixture. Combine olives.
Pour into oiled baking dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix yeast and sugar in hot water.
Add oil, salt and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour and blend well.
Let set for 1 hour with a cover.
Make into rolls and let rise until double in size. Bake in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Roll each chicken breast half and wrap with bacon slice. Fasten with toothpick.
Spread chipped beef on bottom of 9-inch square baking dish.
Place chicken breasts on top of the beef. Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake in a 275° oven for 3 hours.
Remove foil and bake 1 more hour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in broth, chili powder, oregano, cumin, salt and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Dip each tortilla into sauce to coat both sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup of the chicken onto each tortilla around chicken.
Place seam side down in ungreased rectangular baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas; sprinkle with cheese.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven until cheese is melted, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and if desired shredded lettuce.

title: party punch
directions: Mix lemonade and ginger ale together.
Pour in punch bowl with ice mold.
Put scoops of sherbet on top.
Make 1/2 hour before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Mix
and
heat	the
soups,
milk,
mayonnaise and sour cream. Do
not boil these ingredients.
Make layers in casserole dish of	macaroni,
pepper, onion, pimento and soup mixture.
Top
with cheese
(make
2 layers).	Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Cook for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: quick and easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mixed fruit; reserve liquid.
Combine liquid with pudding and Tang.
Stir well.
Gently mix fruit with dressing.
Chill.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in small amount of sugar and lukewarm water. Beat egg.
Mix with balance of sugar and add to yeast.
Pour yeast mixture, lard and potato water into flour and work in until you have a soft dough.
Let rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Place in refrigerator.
Note: I mash my potatoes in the water and use potatoes and water.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press half of crumbs in a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Add diced rhubarb.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla until thick and clear.
Pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve while warm.
Delicious with whipped cream or plain.

title: stuff pepper soup
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and green pepper; stir in tomato soup and water.
Add rice and seasonings.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
You may need to add more water if it is too thick.
This is great served over mashed potatoes for a heartier meal.

title: mama's wilted lettuce
directions: Pour over lettuce with chopped onion.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare bottom crust.
Toss apples and orange juice in a large bowl.
Combine light brown sugar, 1/3 cup granulated sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg.
Toss with apples until coated.
Spoon into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter or oleo.
Moisten edge of pastry with water.
Prepare top crust.
Brush top with milk.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Combine mix, Cool Whip and egg; stir well.
Drop by teaspoon into powdered sugar.
Roll until well coated.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Gently mix together.
Pour into a Pam sprayed casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple-cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apple and cranberry sauce.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar. Place in a baking dish.
Melt margarine and add oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix well and spread over apples and cranberry mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This can be frozen for later use.

title: beef salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Garnish with parsley.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a frying pan; remove.
Combine with bread crumbs, eggs, cheese, salt, pepper (to taste) and parsley.
Meanwhile, cook shells.
Fill each shell with ground beef mixture and place in baking dish which has been spread with about 1 1/2 cups of your favorite spaghetti sauce.
Arrange shells in single layer.
Cover shells with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding as per instructions on package.
Blend in Cool Whip with spatula.
In a 9 x 12-inch baking pan, lay down a layer of graham crackers, spread on a portion of the pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Make another layer of graham crackers and then mixture.
Repeat until mixture is used.
Finish with a layer of graham crackers.
Frost with fudge frosting and refrigerate for a couple of hours before serving.

title: beef roast deluxe
directions: In heavy aluminum foil, lay beef on top. Spread soup mix and mushroom soup.
Seal aluminum foil so no steam escapes.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.
Check doneness of meat.

title: chili soup
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and celery, cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in tomatoes, potatoes, beef broth, water, chili powder, salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Stir in peas or beans and heat through.

title: the freeze
directions: Pour punch in three ice trays and freeze until almost frozen solid.
Take out of trays.
In a blender, put your flavored ice cubes and puree.
Puree until it gets slushy.
Pour into a tumbler and serve.
Serves 1.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Beat sugar, cream, cream cheese and vanilla on low speed until blended, then whip on high speed until stiff.
Fold mixture of other ingredients into cream mixture and chill.

title: raisin pie
directions: Boil raisins in 1 3/4 cups water for 5 minutes.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and salt.
Moisten with 1/4 cup water and add to raisins, stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from fire.
Add butter and vinegar.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan and cover crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken paprikash 1
directions: Use Hungarian imported paprika.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk and sugar to a boil.
Boil, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Place butter and peanut butter chips in double boiler and cook.
After ingredients have melted, remove from heat. Add vanilla, marshmallow cream and walnuts.
Pour marshmallow cream mixture into pan.
Add sugar mixture to top and swirl gently to bottom layer.
Refrigerate until set.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Mix
crab, shrimp, eggs, mayonnaise, Worcestershire and onions.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and dots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden lemon chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then flour.
In skillet, melt butter or margarine and brown chicken 4 minutes, turning once.
Stir in soup mix blended with water.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, covered, 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve with angel hair pasta.

title: coke and honey ham
directions: Trim fat from ham.
Place pineapple slices on top of ham.
Mix brown sugar, dry mustard and honey together.
Spread over ham. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until it begins to brown.
Pour Coke over it and continue the baking for 30 more minutes, basting the last 15 minutes.

title: herbed chicken
directions: Wash chicken (I skin the chicken).
The chicken can be left whole or cut into pieces.
Sprinkle with desired amount of salt and pepper.
Put oil and butter over chicken.
Put cut garlic and the herbs on top.
Cook in oven or on top of stove (the whole chicken is cooked in the oven at 325° until browned).
Baste once in a while.

title: reese's balls
directions: Over low heat, melt oleo.
Stir in milk, vanilla and salt. Mix and remove from heat.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar; stir.
Add peanut butter and syrup.
Mix.
Put remaining 1/2 cup sugar on counter. Pour on mixture and knead until all is mixed in.
Make into balls. Melt chocolate chips and shortening in small pot.
Remove from heat.
Dip balls in chocolate until coated.
Place on pan and refrigerate until firm.
Serve.
Makes 50.

title: homemade tater tots
directions: Combine all ingredients, which should be a stiff dough.
Form into 1-inch balls or drop into hot fat fryer by spoonfuls.
They will puff up and turn golden brown.
Remove from deep fat fryer and drain well on paper towels.
Salt lightly.
Serve as a side dish or use in recipes calling for Tater Tots.

title: spinach and sausage soup
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat, simmer, covered 15 minutes.

title: french meat pie
directions: Fry pork until all pink is gone.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes more.
Drain off fat.
Add seasonings.
Boil potatoes and mash with milk until stiff, not whipped.
Add to meat mixture and blend well.
Put in pie crust.
Cover edges with foil so they won't overcook.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.
Place on cookie sheet in case juices run over.
Delicious.

title: jo's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix all together and let simmer for several hours.
Can be doubled easily.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Rub on whole dry chicken and put some inside of chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes uncovered.

title: peanut butter chip glaze
directions: In small microwave-safe bowl, place peanut butter chips, butter and milk.
Microwave on High power for 45 seconds.
Stir until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Gradually add 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Beat with whisk until smooth.
Drizzle over brownies with peanut butter chips.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash or blend avocados.
Mix in finely chopped onion, tomato and peppers.
Salt to taste.
Chill.

title: turkey appetizers
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cut in butter with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle milk (1 tablespoon at a time) evenly over surface; stir with a fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in turkey, cheese and green pepper.
Drop mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until browned. Serve warm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: 7-up lemon salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together in large bowl.
Can leave in bowl or pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Chill overnight.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Crumble crackers.
Place in mixing bowl and mix in melted margarine.
Place in large greased cake pan.
Pat firmly and set aside.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Run cold water over sauerkraut and drain.
Mix sauerkraut, peppers, onion and celery; set aside.
Boil vinegar and sugar until clear.
Pour over kraut mixture and mix.
Place in jars and refrigerate.

title: rib-and-bean barbecue casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place spareribs in 3-quart buttered casserole.
Mix soy sauce, honey and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Brush some over spareribs.
Bake, covered, for 2 hours.
Meanwhile, saute onions and celery leaves in oil 5 minutes.
Add pepper, seasoning, thyme, 1/4 teaspoon salt, pepper and beans.
At end of 2 hours, remove spareribs; skim surface fat from drippings.
Add bean mixture to casserole.
Top with spareribs.
Brush surface of spareribs with some of the sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes longer. Makes 8 servings.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs.
Blend in melted chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan in a slow oven (325°) for 28 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Cut into 16 squares.
Serves 16.

title: *pepper steak
directions: Flour steak.
Brown in a large skillet on both sides.
Put in other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruity party punch
directions: Combine fruit drinks,
chilled
thoroughly.
Add chilled ginger ale and sherbet at
last minute.
Ladle into punch cups. Serves 25 to 30.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients together.
Combine mixtures.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
You may stuff turkey, 12 to 15 pounds.

title: hamburger dish
directions: Separate biscuits and cut each biscuit in half to get 20 biscuits.
Place 10 on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix meat, sour cream, cooked noodles and vegetables.
Place over bottom layer of biscuits.
Top mixture with remaining biscuits.
Top with the cheese.
Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick coffeecake
directions: Grease pan.
Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and stir. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Put in pan and sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fill greased empty tin or aluminum cans half full (frozen fruit juice cans or soup cans are best).
Cover with a piece of foil.
Place in a large boiler and fill boiler with water halfway up cans.
Boil until bread is firm on top, about 40 minutes. Remove from cans.
Keeps well in refrigerator. Delicious sliced and buttered or toasted.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix all other ingredients with browned meat and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Spread sauce on half of a hamburger bun and top with shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Serves approximately 8 people.

title: peach smoothie
directions: Place the water, lemon juice, and milk in a blender.
Turn on gradually and add peaches and crushed ice.
Blend until smooth. Serve.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Partially cook the broccoli. Set aside and drain.
Mix together the eggs, soup, mushrooms and cheese.
Layer broccoli and cheese mixture and end with cheese on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: honey garlic chicken
directions: Break wings in two places and cut off tips with carving knife. Place in shallow pan and sprinkle with seasonings; dot generously with soya sauce.
Cover with brown sugar and pour on honey; sprinkle with additional garlic powder and soya sauce.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Baste frequently.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onion in butter or oleo in a Dutch oven, over medium heat, until tender, stirring frequently.
Add broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Ladle soup into individual baking dishes.
Top each with a slice of toasted bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Place under broiler 2 or 3 minutes to brown top.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 1/4 cups.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Set in refrigerator to season overnight. Serve with raw vegetables for dipping.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour in bowl. Add beaten egg yolks and milk to flour mixture. Cook in microwave or on medium heat on stove until thick. Then add butter and vanilla to mixture. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: dip for fruits
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, combine egg, sugar and lemon juice. Microwave at 70% power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until mixture boils. Stir.
Microwave 70% of power 30 seconds.
Add extract.
Mix well. Stir well into whipped topping.
This is good as a dressing for fruit salad.

title: rhubarb and sour cream pie
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, tapioca and sour cream.
Add rhubarb and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spicy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cube.
Boil noodles.
Drain water and on low heat stir in remaining ingredients.
Serves 6.

title: creamy pineapple sour cream mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemon juice and sour cream. Beat until blended.
Pour into freezer tray.
Quickly chill mixture for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm 1-inch from edge and still soft in center.
Pour into bowl and whip until fluffy. Fold in pineapple.
Pour into 1-quart mold and chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: classic red beans
directions: Wash beans in a strainer and discard any grit or discolored beans.
Put beans and the rest of the ingredients in an 8-quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Stirring often, cook beans about 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender and creamy.
Serve over fluffy long grain rice.
You can also put a good dollop of sour cream on top of your serving of red beans and rice.
It's delicious!

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in buttered, shallow dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Combine soup, sour cream and mushrooms; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika, almonds and Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Crush crackers.
Beat 3 egg whites stiff and add sugar, baking powder, and vanilla; mix.
Add pecans.
Fold in crackers.
Pour mixture into 9-inch greased pie plate.
Bake 40 minutes at 300°. When cool, refrigerate.
Serve topped with Cool Whip.

title: crabbies
directions: Split and lightly toast English muffins.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and spread on toasted English muffins.
Cut into eighths.
Bake in 350° oven until brown and bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: joan lunden's poppercosh
directions: Saute butter, onion and green pepper.
Add paprika, tomatoes, potatoes, hot dogs or chicken and water to cover.
Cook until potatoes are done.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix the 1/2 cup white sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a dish. Cut biscuits into fourths and roll each piece in cinnamon sugar. Drop in a greased Bundt pan.
Melt margarine, brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in saucepan.
Pour into biscuits.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Monkey bread may be pulled apart instead of cutting.

title: joe's roasted vidalia onions on grill
directions: Peel onion and garlic.
On piece of aluminum wrap, large enough to enclose onion, place whole onion, whole garlic cloves, butter and white pepper.
Wrap and put in grill for an hour.
Serve in foil.
Onions are best if roasted until quite dark.
Aroma released when foil is opened is wonderful!

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: Mix should be taken in daily doses or in extreme need, take a large dose hourly.

title: reese's cup bars
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, sugar and graham cracker crumbs together.
Mix thoroughly and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips and spread on top.

title: chicken enchilada bake
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Add olives, chilies, soup and sour cream.
Mix well.
(Reserve 3/4 cup of this sauce.)
Add chicken and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix well.
Warm tortillas.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Roll up, place seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine reserved sauce, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat; mix well.
Pour over enchiladas.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: purple cows
directions: Fill glasses 2/3 full with grape juice. Add 2 scoops of ice cream to each glass.
Serve with ice tea spoons.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat milk, cinnamon, eggs, brown sugar and salt together.
Add mashed sweet potatoes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mrs. field's creamy lemon macadamia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well with a wire whisk and set aside.
In a large bowl, blend sugars well with an electric mixer set at medium speed.
Add the butter and cream cheese; mix to form a smooth paste.
Add the egg and lemon extract; beat at medium speed until light and soft.
Scrape down sides of bowl occasionally.
Add the flour mixture and Macadamia nuts.
Blend at low speed just until combined.
Do not overmix.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Melt butter.
Heat oven to 325°.
Dissolve soda in hot water.
Beat egg in small bowl.
In large bowl, mix ingredients in order listed except for cranberries and nuts; mix well.
Add cranberries and nuts and mix again.
Pour into loaf pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mumbles
directions: Beat the butter and sugar to a creamy mixture.
Add the beaten egg and lemon rind.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Drop by spoonfuls on a greased pan and bake about 10 minutes at 350°.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown sausage, drain off grease.
Add beef and finish browning with onion; drain again.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings to saucepan and simmer 15 minutes.
Toast tops of split buns under broiler.
Place hot meat mixture on split sides of buns, to the edge.
Top with grated cheese and place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve immediately, open-faced.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spotted owl and rice bake
directions: Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour 1/2 into ungreased baking dish 9 x 12-inch.
Add rice, mushrooms with juice and 1/2 the onion soup mix.
Top with owl breasts.
Pour soup mix over top and sprinkle remaining onion soup mix on.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: grandma leonard's apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand for 15 to 20 minutes. Beat eggs slightly.
Stir in oil and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in apples and oil mixture alternately. Stir in nuts.
Spoon into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: layered tossed salad
directions: Tear lettuce in small pieces and put in oblong dish.
Add frozen peas, then onion, then celery, chestnuts and bacon.
Cover with mayonnaise and sprinkle sugar over.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Let set at least 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator. Will keep fresh about 1 week.

title: banana delight cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese, milk and pudding until stiff.
Spread on cake.
Next, spread pineapple and banana on cake.
Top this with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in a 2-quart dish.
Cover top with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: aunt pearl krienke's brown sugar cookies
directions: Bake at 350°.
May be baked in shallow pan and cut while still warm, or dropped by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.

title: yeast raised biscuits
directions: In a small bowl combine yeast, sugar and water.
Let stand until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: quick potato rolls
directions: Mix together the milk and potatoes; add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add dry ingredients and mix until easy to handle. Shape into desired shapes and let rise until doubled (45 to 60 minutes).
Bake until golden brown at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 1 1/2 dozen rolls.
(Measure leftover mashed potatoes into 1 cup portions and freeze for later use in recipes.)

title: fried peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise in half.
Remove seeds.
Slice lengthwise into one-inch wide strips.
Cut onions into thick slices.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add peppers, onions and garlic. Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until softened.
Season with salt, pepper and vinegar, then stir.

title: fresh vegetable marinade
directions: Remove flowerets from broccoli; cut into bite size pieces. Reserve stalks for other use.
Combine all vegetables; toss lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Garnish with celery leaves and tomatoes.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: chile verde
directions: Trim off fat; cut pork into cubes.
Heat oil in heavy pan or Dutch oven.
Add pork; cook until brown.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in flour.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes. Add stewed tomatoes, chopped chilies and Mexican tomatoes with hot chilies.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover; cook for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can wrap in flour tortillas and top with grated cheese.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Whip butter and sugar for 1 minute.
Add syrup and salt; beat 1 minute.
Add eggs, beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Add nuts, pour in shell and bake for approximately 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Put 1 cup mixture in blender; puree and then gradually add the rest. Add instant chicken broth or cube.
Then add evaporated milk; add salt, pepper, butter and curry to taste.
May be served hot or cold.
Serves 6.

title: meat pot pie
directions: Brown beef with diced onion and green pepper.
Drain fat.
Add garlic, onion soup mix, corn, salt and pepper.
Mix all together and heat through.
Pour into casserole dish and top with mashed potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes until potatoes are browned.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Place in bowl in order shown with mayonnaise last.
Place enough mayonnaise over mixture to cover all, leaving none exposed. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: parmesan potato rounds
directions: Pour margarine into a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
In a large plastic bag, combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper.
Shake a few potato slices at a time in the bag to coat.
Place potatoes in single layer over the margarine.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Turn slices and sprinkle with Italian seasonings.
Bake 30 minutes more until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Bake pie shell and coat with margarine; set aside.
Separate yolks and whites of eggs.
Put whites in freezer part of refrigerator immediately and they will be cold enough to beat after other ingredients are mixed.
Beat other ingredients together.
Boil, stirring constantly; when thick, pour into pie shell.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Pound chicken breasts between waxed paper until thin.
Place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Provolone or Swiss cheese on each. Roll up.
Then roll in melted margarine and then in bread crumb mixture (bread crumbs, grated cheese and spices).
Place seam side down in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese filling
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Heat shortening.
Season and brown pork chops on both sides. Place chops in greased oven dish.
Place onion rings and bell pepper on each chop.
Fill each ring with about 2 tablespoons rice.
Pour tomato juice around in dish.
Cover with celery. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Put basil, oil, garlic, pine nuts and salt in a blender.
Blend until smooth.
Put mixture into a bowl and add cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Can be doubled.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pudding mix to Cool Whip; stir well.
Add pineapple and juice, chopped nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill.

title: fruit mix
directions: Drain and save juices of peaches and pineapple.
Cut peaches into bite-sizes.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups juices.
Mix Tang with pudding.
(It dissolves better.) Pour over fruit and mix. Let set overnight.

title: golden banana cake
directions: Mix together. Pour into bundt pan. Bake at 325 degrees about 50 min.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cube potatoes and cook in small amount of water until they are barely tender. Melt margarine and add flour and salt. Add milk and cook on low heat until mixture begins to thicken. Add cheese and let melt. Drain potatoes and put in greased dish. Put the onions and pimentos on top. You may sprinkle black pepper on top if you wish. Pour cheese sauce over potatoes. Cover and cook at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Remove cover and cook another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mint fondue
directions: Heat honey and cream or half and half in a pan over medium flame.
Lower heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted.
Stir in vanilla, mint extract and creme de menthe.
Pour into fondue pot; keep warm enough for dipping.

title: baked herb chicken
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: seafood muffins
directions: Melt butter and cheese together.
Add garlic and crabmeat.
Let sit until set.
Spread on 4 English muffins.
May freeze (this may make them neater for cutting).
Cut into 6 pieces and broil until golden.

title: kool-lemonade punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid following package directions using club soda for water.
Mix in lemonade using club soda for water.
Makes approximately 3 quarts.

title: tequila sunrise
directions: Pour tequila and orange juice over ice.
Add grenadine and stir.
Makes 1 drink.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Use a Bundt pan or any type tube pan.
Grease or spray well.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, mix apples and eggs.
Add sugar, cinnamon, salad oil and nuts.
Mix flour, salt, soda and sift into apple mixture.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order as given.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator up to 12 hours.
If desired, toss and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, oil and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients. Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cheeses with rest of ingredients and shape into a ball using half the pecans and parsley.
Roll in remaining pecans and parsley.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine flour, the first 1/4 teaspoon of sweet basil, garlic salt and the 1/2 teaspoon of pepper.
Dredge pieces of chicken in flour mixture.
Brown on both sides in hot oil.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar and oleo.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add sour cream.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Pour half of batter into pan.
Mix pecans, cinnamon and sugar and sprinkle half of it on top of batter.
Pour in balance of batter and sprinkle balance of cinnamon mixture on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: the perfect ambulance call
directions: Quickly combine all ingredients for a rapid response to the scene.
Administer efficient quality care to the patient.
Package the patient and put in the ambulance at a climate controlled temperature of 70°.
After safely arriving at the hospital, transfer patient to the emergency room where patient will be treated in less than 2 hours and released with a healthy appetite to enjoy our recipes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk for 3 minutes.
Remove from stove and add crushed saltines, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat well and pour in pan.
Use 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan, depending upon the thickness you want the fudge to be.

title: christmas cranberry float
directions: In a four-quart pitcher or punch bowl, combine liquids.
Add sherbet and ice as desired just before serving.

title: monkey bread #2
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters; mix sugar and cinnamon together in a large mixing bowl.
Toss in biscuit quarters and coat each piece well with dry mixture.
In a greased Bundt pan, place the cherries evenly around pan.
Place biscuit pieces in Bundt pan a layer at a time, putting nuts in between each layer of biscuit quarters.
Repeat this until all pieces are in pan evenly.
Melt butter; stir in remaining sugar mixture.
Let sugar dissolve.
Pour over biscuit quarters.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert onto serving plate and pull apart to eat.

title: strawberry pecan salad
directions: Heat pineapple over medium heat.
Add gelatin mix; let cool. Add pecans, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill overnight.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Add jello to water; add frozen strawberries.
Stir until berries separate and let stand in refrigerator until set, but not thoroughly jelled.
Spoon over cake and refrigerate.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
In large skillet, brown cubed steak and sliced onions in oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until onions are tender.

title: easy elegant cookies
directions: Cut graham crackers in 4's.
Place on cookie sheet so they touch.
Melt butter and sugar in pan until frothy.
Pour over the graham crackers.
Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove after 30 seconds.
Transfer to cool on waxed paper.

title: pop's ham 'n potato scallop
directions: Boil potatoes for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Blend soup, milk and pepper; add ham.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake about 15 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: sweet pie dough for tarts
directions: Cream margarine and sugar;
add eggs and milk, then add dry ingredients.
Add flour to form ball.

title: * hamburger pie *
directions: Brown onion in hot fat.
Add meat and seasoning and brown; drain well.
Add drained green beans and tomato sauce.
Pour into greased casserole.
Mash potatoes; add milk, egg and seasonings (salt and pepper).
Spoon in mounds over meat.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: liver loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake in loaf pan in moderate oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer ingredients, starting with spinach, then in this order, the tomatoes, onion, 1/2 of cheese, peas and bacon bits.
Pour Ranch dressing on top, then top with rest of cheese.
Good if it is fixed the night before and put in the icebox.

title: fat free brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, sift together cocoa powder, cinnamon, flour, cream of tartar and baking soda.
Set aside.

title: texas savory chicken
directions: Heat oil
in
Dutch
oven over medium heat. Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken; add onion, celery and carrots and
saute
minutes.
Add
tomatoes, tomato paste, wine, salt,
pepper and cinnamon.
Bring sauce and vegetables to boil. Return
chicken to pan.
Bake in 350° oven, covered, about 1
1/2 hours
or
until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease. Serve with pasta.
Serves 4.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in oleo, then add onion, celery and mushrooms; brown until tender.
Add juice from bean sprouts plus enough water to make 1 1/2 cups, salt and molasses.
Cook on low heat until meat is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup water. Add soy sauce.
Stir into meat.
Cook for 7 minutes or until thick. Serve over rice.

title: gougeres(miniature cheese popovers)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grate cheese.
In a medium size saucepan, bring the water, butter, salt, pepper and nutmeg to a boil.
When butter has melted, remove from heat.
Add all the flour to butter-water mixture; beat with a wooden spoon until mixture leaves sides of pan clean.
Add cheese; beat until incorporated.
Beat in 4 of the eggs, one by one, until thoroughly absorbed.
Beat until mixture is smooth, shiny and firm.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.

title: fresh polish sausage
directions: *Use 10 pounds meat.
You can use all pork if you want.

title: pumpkin bread #2
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared (small) loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour/60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: creamy double cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat to mix well. Combine remaining ingredients and stir into egg mixture.
Turn into greased and heated 9-inch square baking pan. Bake in preheated 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until well browned. Leftover pieces can be reheated nicely. Serves 6 to 8.

title: graham cracker crispies
directions: Using a broiler pan, cover with aluminum foil, lay graham crackers over entire surface.

Bring to a boil, butter and sugar and boil for 4 minutes. When thickened, pour over crackers. Use a pastry brush if necessary to help spread. Sprinkle with pecans to your taste. Bake in a 350° oven 10 minutes. Let cool slightly then remove from pan. If left in pan too long they will harden and stick.

title: cream cheese pound cake 2
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Spray 10 inch tube pan with non-stick spray.
In a large bowl, cream together butter, margarine, and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time mixing well after each addition. Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Check at one hour for doneness.
Sharp knife inserted at center comes out clean.

title: beverly's veggie omelet
directions: Grease dish; drain Ro-Tel and pour in dish.
Mix eggs, Bisquick mix, milk and salt together until fluffy.
Pour over Ro-Tel.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Great for breakfast.

title: dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine and place in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle graham crumbs evenly over margarine.
Pour condensed milk over the graham crumbs.
Top it off with the coconut, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: barbecue shredded beef
directions: Cook meat until very tender in water to which salt has been added.
While meat is cooking, make sauce.
Melt shortening and add onions; cook until tender, but not browned.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Add shredded meat and liquid to the sauce and mix well.
Cover and cook very slowly for 30 minutes.
If mixture becomes too thick, add a little water.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: egg rolls
directions: Cut cabbage, broccoli and mushrooms into small pieces.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Add meat.
Add salt and pepper if desired.
Let cool down.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together, roll into a ball and chill about 2 hours; roll in chopped nuts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together mayo, sour cream, soup and spinach.
Let sit in fridge until soup mix is softened, about 1 hour.
Stir before serving.

title: spiced cupcakes
directions: Cook the raisins in 3 cups water and boil for 5 minutes; drain and cool.
To 1 1/2 cups raisin water, add baking soda.
Then alternately add flour, spices and nuts along with the raisins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Tastes real good with a buttercream frosting.

title: spaghetti ala carbonara
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Meanwhile, fry bacon over moderate heat until crisp; drain all but 1 tablespoon of fat. Add the red pepper, if used, and the half and half.
Keep warm in skillet.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in remaining ingredients for 1 hour. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: donna's goulash
directions: Skillet method takes about 1 1/2 hours.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Prepare 24 hours before time to serve.
In large size bowl, layer lettuce, onions, peas, water chestnuts, eggs
and Miracle Whip, then sprinkle sugar on top with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let set for 24 hours, then toss before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and lard well.
Beat egg and add vinegar and water.
Pour over flour mixture.
Bake at 425°.
Makes 4 pie shells.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Bring to a boil on high heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil slowly, stirring gradually, until mixture forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Let stand until cooled a little. Add peanut butter and beat until fudge thickens.
Pour into slightly buttered pan or platter.
Let cool thoroughly before cutting into squares.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Ready to use after setting 24 hours.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Sift together flour and cornstarch.
Beat eggs slightly; add beer.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Dip fish in batter and deep fry or fry in skillet.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Bring first three ingredients to a boil.
Add jello while mixture is hot.
Refrigerate until set.
Stir with a spoon and add celery.
Add cheese, nutmeats and Cool Whip.

title: homemade bread
directions: Soften the yeast in lukewarm water and milk.
Add sugar, salt and melted butter; mix well.
Add sifted flour gradually, beating thoroughly after each addition until dough is just stiff enough to knead.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover and set in warm place until doubled in bulk.
Work down lightly.
Form into desired size loaves and place in well-oiled pans.
Cover with wax paper; set in warm place.
Let rise and, when doubled in bulk, bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat slightly and continue baking 1/2 hour longer. (Four to 4 1/2 hours are required for the entire process, but it's worth it!)
Makes one large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: steak marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients. Poke holes in steaks with fork. Put steaks in plastic bag and pour marinade into bag. Soak overnight for best flavor.

title: weight watchers broccoli cheese soup
directions: Dissolve Butter Buds in one cup water.
Add another 7 cups water and remaining ingredients except broccoli .
Mix and cook 1 hour.
Add broccoli cuts.
Cook until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Stir in 1 pound Velveeta light, cut into cubes.
Simmer until melted.
Do not boil.
One cup equals 1 protein and 1/2 bread.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Soften cheese and mix with sugar.
Fold into Cool Whip and spread into crust.
Can be served immediately.
Pour cherry topping over each individual slice.
Quick, easy and delicious!

title: spicy beef
directions: Slice steak into 2 x 1 inch strips. (Place in freezer for 1/2 hour before cutting, makes slicing easier.) Heat skillet and add oil. Add peppers and ginger to the oil: fry until peppers turn brown. Add the garlic and beef strips, fry until brown. Sprinkle with sherry; and salt, sugar and soy sauce. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until sauce is almost gone, about 20 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Cut one side of dates with a knife; spread apart.
Cream sugar, butter and salt until very light and fluffy.
Add orange rind, nuts and extract.
Stuff each date generously, then press 2 whole dates together to make one, and roll each in powdered sugar. Let stand several hours before serving.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: dump cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Add sugar, flour and milk. Mix together well.
Dump fruit pie filling in center.
Do not stir!
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: crabbies
directions: Soften butter and cheese.
Pick over crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread over split muffins.
Freeze 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut each muffin into quarters.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When ready to serve, broil (frozen) until bubbly.
If making ahead, muffins can be stored in freezer bags.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed on box in 2 (8 x 9-inch) round pans. When cake cools, pierce with fork.
Pour Kahlua over cakes.
Cool with plastic over it and refrigerate overnight.
Make mousse using 4 cups milk.
In large bowl, place one of the round cakes on bottom of bowl.
Layer with half of the mousse and 1/3 of the candy, then a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat same process (cutting the other layer of cake in little pieces).
Cake, mousse, candy, Cool Whip, then top with remaining crushed candy bar.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Eight boxes of mousse with 4 cups milk may be used to make a thicker, richer mousse.

title: hob-goblin doughnuts
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Stir in milk and melted Crisco.
Blend in combined dry ingredients and mix until smooth.
Roll on a floured board to 3/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured doughnut cutter.
Cut one doughnut, interlock with a second doughnut and seal loose ends with milk.
Fry in deep fat heated to 365° until brown, 3 to 5 minutes.

title: mom's pasta
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add garlic, sugar, parsley, oregano, tomatoes, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce and mushrooms; simmer 1 hour.
Cook macaroni.
Drain.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with sauce.
Then layer half of the Provolone (overlapping), sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with more sauce.
Repeat, keeping the Mozzarella for the top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take foil off to brown.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: You will need lots of paper towels.

title: chili
directions: Soak beans in cold water overnight. Parboil 15 minutes in the morning. Cook ground beef, onion and green peppers until lightly browned.
Drain beans. Add to ground beef mixture.
Add balance of ingredients and cook in crock-pot for several hours.

title: pig licking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Beat together the cream cheese and sugar, then add 8 ounces sour cream; beat until blended.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon and set aside.
Peel and slice apples and set aside.
Cream sugar and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix baking powder and flour together and add this alternately with orange juice.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a greased tube pan; use batter first, then apples, then sugar/cinnamon mixture. Layer until all is used.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°, then 1 hour at 350°. This keeps well.

title: pineapple souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and add slices of bread, cubed.
Leave on stove until slightly toasted.
Beat whole eggs slightly; add sugar, flour and pineapple, including all the juice. Place a layer of egg mixture in well buttered baking dish, then layer of bread.
Repeat, ending with bread on top.
Bake 1 hour.

title: pastry
directions: Mix flour, salt, and sugar.
Cut in butter with knife. Sprinkle several drops lemon juice and small amount of water.
Form into ball and chill.
Roll onto lightly floured board.
Makes 2 (9-inch) crusts or 1 double.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Grind up first 3 ingredients.
Drain for 1 hour.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, sugar and spice.
Add to ground mixture.
Boil for 20 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: cream cheese corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown and scramble ground round. Drain well. Add onion and bell pepper. Cover and cook on med/low heat until onion and pepper are tender. Add beans, celery salt and other seasonings. Cover and continue to cook over low heat 15 minutes. Serves up great with corn bread.

title: appetizer potato bites
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cook, covered, in boiling water for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender; drain
and
cool.	Cut potatoes in half; place halves in the egg
tray.
Spread
1 teaspoon of the avocado dip over each potato.
Then top with cherry tomato and parsley. Apply seal; chill until serving time.

title: amish pudding
directions: Mix the dates, hot water and soda.
Add the sugar, flour, eggs and butter.
Combine and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, then cool.

title: glazed pecans
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg white, sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, ground cloves and nuts. Stir to coat nuts with the egg and spice mixture. Spread on a greased cookie sheet. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Then sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter; pour Eagle Brand condensed milk over graham cracker crumbs.
Pour chocolate chips over top of milk.
Then pour butterscotch or peanut butter chips over top of chocolate chips.
Then pour walnuts over top of all that.
Press all that down firmly with a fork.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then cut into bars.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Brown hamburger; add sauce. Simmer. Cook jumbo shells and drain. Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish lightly with nonstick spray. Fill jumbo shells with a teaspoon of cottage cheese and a teaspoon of meat mixture. Place filled shells, in rows, in baking dish. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and bake an additional 5 minutes. Let set 10 minutes before serving.

title: steamed clams a la marniere
directions: Allow 1/2 to 1 quart unshelled clams per person.
Be sure clams are alive (no open or damaged shells).
Wash and scrub shells well and rinse several times.
Place in large kettle and add enough wine to make 1/2-inch in bottom.
Add butter, onion, parsley, thyme, bay leaf and peppercorns.
Steam in tightly covered kettle, just until shells open.
Remove and discard any closed shells.
Strain broth and serve with the clams.
You may dip unshelled clams in melted butter.

title: mother's weekday cake
directions: Sift together flour and baking powder.
Cream together sugar, eggs, cream and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Bake until toothpick comes clean.

title: sesame honey vegetable casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thaw and place mixed vegetables in a shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese, in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes or until heated through. Serves 6.

title: almond brickle(can be made on the run)
directions: Sprinkle almonds in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Melt butter in a large, heavy saucepan, over medium heat.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly for 7 minutes.
Pour over almonds.
Cool 5 minutes.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Let stand 5 minutes until morsels become shiny and soft; spread evenly over top.
When cool, refrigerate 20 minutes to set chocolate.

title: recipe for happiness
directions: Sprinkle generously with kindness.
Add plenty of faith (in a Supreme Being and in yourself) and mix well.
Spread this combination over the period of a lifetime and serve everyone that you meet.

title: real fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
Sprinkle each piece with salt, pepper, cayenne and garlic and rub it in.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 to 3 hours before cooking.
Heat the lard in a large iron skillet to 375° or until it just starts to smoke lightly.
Just before frying, dredge pieces lightly in flour and fry 2 to 3 pieces at a time.
Breasts take 12 to 15 minutes, drumsticks and backs 9 to 10 minutes.
Pieces can be kept warm in a 200° oven while frying others.

title: bagali polo(rice with lima beans)
directions: Parboil long grain rice until it is tender but slightly chewy, (about 12 minutes), drain, rinse and set aside.
Steam or microwave lima beans as directed on the box.
Reserving 1 cup of rice, mix remaining rice, lima beans, salt and the dried dill weed.
Melt 1/4 cup of butter into the pot in which you cooked the rice.
Pour the reserved rice in and spread it over the bottom of the pan.
Spoon in the rice mixture, sprinkle 2 tablespoons of water over all.
Put 2 to 3 paper towels over the pot, cover tightly.
Try to fold the paper towels up so they don't catch fire.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes at medium heat.
Lower the heat and continue to cook for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Mix ingredients together and bring to boil.
Boil a little. Keeps 1 month.

title: ham and macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Add ham and continue to heat through.
Serve with bread and butter or a salad.
A very quick and inexpensive dinner for those who's time is limited. Serves 4.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix in all the ingredients. Pour in meat loaf pan.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 20 or 30 minutes or until done.

title: spinach parmesan casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Melt margarine; saute onion until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add spinach and next 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and bacon bits, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Fold in Crispix cereal until coated.
Put powdered sugar in large paper or plastic bag. Add cereal mixture and shake until well covered.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut center out of loaf of bread.
Place mixture in center of bread.
Cut bread removed from center into cubes and put around loaf on the serving tray.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown meats, onion and pepper; drain.
While that is browning, mix catsup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard; add to crock-pot. To this add beans.
For best results, a minimum of 3 cans of beans is needed, one of which must be baked beans, not pork 'n beans. Add meat mixture and stir well but gently.
Cook on low for 4 hours in crock-pot or bake covered in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Serve with salad and cornbread for a meal.

title: sidewalk chalk
directions: To make white chalk:
Mix together plaster of Paris and water until the mix is about as thick as toothpaste or mashed potatoes. (If it seems too runny, add 1 tablespoon of plaster at a time until it's thick enough.
If it seems too thick, add a small amount of water.)
Set the cardboard tube upright on the waxed paper.
Spoon the mix into the tube.
Try to pop or push out any bubbles.
Let the filled tube rest upright on the waxed paper for 3 to 4 hours until the chalk has set.
Then, peel off the cardboard (it will be damp).
Let the chalk dry completely for 24 hours.

title: soft buns
directions: Mix with mixer.
In large bowl, thoroughly mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, dry yeast and margarine.
Gradually add water and beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl.
Add 3/4 cup flour and beat on high speed 2 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough, not too stiff.
With a spoon take out and put on a floured board and knead until smooth.
Put in a greased bowl and grease top; let rise in warm place until doubled in size, about 45 minutes.
Punch down; let rise again.
Make buns, let rise and bake at 375° until brown and done, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: wassail
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer
10 more minutes.
Strain and serve.
Makes your house smell great.

title: beef and vegetable tortilla casserole
directions: In a 12-inch skillet on high heat, brown meat, onion and garlic.
Add chili powder and cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and juice, corn, kidney beans, oregano and salt.
Bring to a boil on high heat, then simmer for 10 minutes on reduced heat.
Put mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cut tortillas in 1-inch strips and lay on top of beef mixture.
Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Cream eggs, confectioners sugar and butter.
Then gently add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Lastly add the nuts.
Crush vanilla wafers and sprinkle over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover crumbs with first mixture and sprinkle a few crumbs of vanilla wafers.
Let set overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
In a saucepan, heat milk. Gradually add dry ingredients, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks slowly as not to cause lumps.
Cook until desired consistency. Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, Crisco and sugars.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and pour in skillet. Bake at 450° in oven until done.

title: fried apple rings
directions: Cut ends from apples and slice each apple crosswise into 4 rings.
In large skillet, melt butter and stir in sugar and cinnamon.
Add layer of apple slices and cook over medium heat, turning once, until golden and tender but still intact.
Stack slices at side of skillet when almost done and cook remaining apples. Serve warm topped with pan juices.
Good with sausage links or patties, pork chops, ham or pancakes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion soup and hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-chicken stir-fry
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Combine juice and cornstarch. Add soy sauce, honey, vinegar and pepper; mix well.
Set aside. Heat oil in wok.
Add green peppers; stir-fry 2 minutes and remove.
Add more oil if necessary; cook chicken until done.
Add soy mixture to chicken.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Add peppers and pineapple.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve with rice.

title: cherry vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks in a medium saucepan. Cook over medium heat until thickened (bubbles appear).
Cool to room temperature and add half and half, vanilla and cherries, including juice.
Freeze in crank type freezer per manufacturer's instructions.

title: pea salad
directions: Pinch lettuce apart and cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add layer of peas.
Combine chopped cucumber, pepper and onion in separate bowl, then add on top of peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over salad.
Sprinkle Accent and Season-All.
Place cheese on top.
Add bacon bits when ready to eat.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium size, nonstick skillet, brown beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Transfer beef and onion to 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, about 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: red sparkler
directions: Shake well.
Serve in tall glass over ice.
Garnish with celery stalk.
Serves 1.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, baking cocoa and sugar well. Add milk, butter and yolks, well beaten. Let come to a boil; take from stove and pour into baked pie crusts.

title: blueberry sour-cream cake
directions: Position rack in the center of the oven.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix green chiles with cream cheese.
Spread a thin layer over a tortilla.
Roll into tube tightly.
Cut into about 1/2-inch sections.
Repeat until mixture is gone.
Serve with salsa or hot sauce.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses set at room temperature until softened enough to blend together.
Mix all ingredients together into a ball.
Roll in pecans.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix gelatin, cornstarch and sugar in saucepan.
Add 1 cup of boiling water.
Stir over low heat, until it thickens.
Cool completely.
Fill pie crust with strawberries.
Pour gelatin mixture over berries.
Refrigerate until completely chilled. Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Thoroughly mix and let chill.

title: lizzy layer dip
directions: Mash together avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Then mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
On large plate, layer bean dip (spread out), avocado mix (spread out on top bean dip), sour cream, green onion, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: ice cream cake roll
