directions: Grease 2 jelly roll pans.
Line bottoms with waxed paper and grease and flour.
Beat eggs until thick in large bowl.
Mix in water; add cake mix.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake in 350° oven until cake begins to pull away from sides of pans, about 15 to 18 minutes.
Invert on towels.
Cool 8 to 10 minutes, no longer. Spread cakes with ice cream; sprinkle with your choice of berries, pressing lightly into the ice cream.
Roll up and freeze.
Slice and garnish with fresh berries.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash tomatoes; slice 1/2-inch thick.
Dust with flour.
Dip in egg; coat with cracker crumbs.
Fry in the oil, turning until golden brown.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: zucchini noodle casserole
directions: Cook onion, zucchini and peppers in stick of butter until well done.
Cook noodles according to package; drain and mix with vegetables.
Add sour cream.
Put in Pam-sprayed casserole dish. Put cheese over top.
Bake 20 minutes to 1/2 hour at 350°.
May be microwaved to let cheese melt.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in tight container.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and pour into greased square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients with mixer and place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put all ingredients in large plastic bag.
Shake well.
Place coated potatoes in a shallow baking dish; discard bag.
Bake 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with parsley if desired.

title: danish veal "birds" (benlose fugle)
directions: Pound meat well.
Saute onion lightly in butter.
Add bread crumbs, parsley, celery, salt and water to make a dressing.
Cut meat in four pieces, placing dressing on each piece.
Roll up the meat and fasten with toothpicks.
Season and roll in flour.
Brown well in a pan and add water and the undiluted soup.
Cover and simmer until tender (about 1 hour), adding water if needed.
You can also fill the "birds" with bacon or leeks.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add cream cheese.
Blend with hand mixer until smooth.
Stir in other ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet. Put browned ground beef and all other ingredients together in large pot or crock-pot. Cook on low all day.

title: orange glaze
directions: Put icing sugar and orange juice into a small mixing bowl. Add vanilla and stir with a wooden spoon. Add grated orange peel with wooden spoon.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix Miracle Whip with sugar and lemon juice.
Stir into broccoli and other food.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix brown sugar, molasses, salt and hot water together in large bowl.
Cool until warm (110° to 115°).
Meanwhile, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add rye flour to liquid; beat well.
Add yeast and caraway seed; mix well.
Add white flour to make a medium soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic, adding more white flour, if needed, about 10 minutes.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk (about 1 hour).
Punch down and let rise again (about 30 minutes).
Punch down again and cut into 5 pieces. Shape into round loaves.
Place on opposite ends of greased cookie sheets.
Cover.
Let rise until double again, about 1 hour. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in center of oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
Yield:
5 loaves.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: Drain berries; reserve syrup.
Add water to syrup to measure 1 cup.
In small saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually add strawberry syrup, stirring until smooth.
Over low heat, slowly bring to boiling, stirring, until mixture is thickened and translucent.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries and strawberry preserves.
Stir until preserves are melted. Refrigerate until cold.
Makes 1 1/3 cups.

title: coconut oatmeal drops
directions: Combine sugar, shortening, eggs and flavoring in bowl and beat until fluffy.
Stir in rolled oats and coconut.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Drop the stiff dough on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen crisp cookies.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Toast pecans for 10 minutes at 300°.
Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans.
Cook until it spins a thread.
Remove and add nuts and vanilla quickly.
Pour onto buttered dish.

title: pot roast beef
directions: Sear meat on both sides in iron pot or skillet with cover; add vinegar and wine.
Simmer for 1 hour at low heat (300°).
Cover with sour cream.
Baste every once in a while.
When starting to get tender, add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Up heat to 350° and cook until meat is very tender and vegetables are done.
Serve with a dry Bordeaux wine.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend everything, except peanuts.
Fold peanuts in by hand. Serve with Granny Smith apple slices (unpeeled).

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Prepare frosting before mixing cake and refrigerate.

title: cheesy pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet with shortening. Cover breadboard with pastry cloth, tucking ends underneath. Cover rolling pin with stockinet cover.
For convenience, place some flour in custard cup.
Sprinkle the covered board and rolling pin lightly with the flour and rub it in until it disappears.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat with an eggbeater.
Cut 1 clove of garlic and add.
Let stand about 2 hours and then strain.
Chill until ready to toss with your favorite green salad.

title: cheesy onion dip
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Then combine with all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
Makes about a pint.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Beat in eggs, cocoa, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients. Add and beat in well.
Fold in zucchini. Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: atomic hot wings by uncle joe
directions: Cut and separate wings.
Batter wings in seasoned flour (flour, salt, pepper, ginger, garlic and cayenne pepper).
Deep fry in hot oil 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Dice all peppers very small; put into a saucepan with the butter.
Cook over low heat until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Add cayenne and black peppers, chili powder, cumin, garlic, ginger and Texas Pete; cook another 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Pour over wings and toss.
Place in oven at 325° for 15 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Can be frozen and heated in microwave. Preparation time is 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 7 to 10 dozen.
Good luck!

title: no peek casserole
directions: Preheat oven at 300°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put into 3-quart casserole.
Put in oven and cook for 3 hours.
Stir once during cooking time.
Serve with mashed potatoes or noodles.

title: shrimp and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Add soup, lemon juice, pepper, onion, milk and butter.
Stir over low flame.
Add parsley and shrimp.
Pour into well-greased casserole.
Top with green pepper rings.
(Parboil green peppers with 6 garlics and 1 teaspoon salt.)
Sprinkle with 4 cups grated cheese.
Dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: rosemary beef with shallot sauce
directions: Season steak pieces with pepper, rosemary and garlic salt. Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shallots and red pepper; saut until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add steak and saut 2 to 3 minutes or until slightly browned.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Remove from heat and mix in sour cream and cream cheese.
Garnish with fresh rosemary sprigs, if desired.

title: marion's cucumber relish
directions: Put cucumbers and onions through food chopper.
Add salt.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric.
Boil 5 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: easy scalloped corn
directions: Mix all together and pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Warm broccoli through and drain. Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 1 hour.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add mayonnaise to moisten and salt to taste.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients. Finish filling 1 gallon can of hand electric freezer to desired level with milk.
Freeze, then pack in ice and salt or put in freezer.
Can change the fruit to banana and add nuts for banana nut ice cream.

title: pizza dough
directions: Mix yeast, salt and sugar.
Measure warm water and oil; add to yeast mixture.
Add 1 cup flour.
Beat 1 minute; rest 3 minutes. Add flour until it leaves side of bowl.
Knead dough.
Put in container.
Bake on greased pan at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hot peppers
directions: Sweeten to taste. Heat and pour over peppers packed in jars.

title: curtis's rice and sausage
directions: Cook rice and drain. Chop sausage up fine, add to rice and stir. Add cheese, salt and pepper. Stir and serve.

title: fudge nougat
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook for exactly 10 minutes, stirring often with spatula for even stirring.
Stir in remaining ingredients and spread into vegetable sprayed pan, 11 x 7 or 12 x 8-inch.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, pineapple and soy sauce in saucepan. Cook until bubbly.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water in measuring cup.
Add gradually to pineapple mixture.
Cook until thickened to desired consistency, stirring constantly.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: red velvet punch
directions: Thaw frozen orange, pineapple and lemon juices. Combine in large container. Add cranberry juice and grape juice. Stir until mixed well. Chill. Just before serving, add chilled ginger ale. Red food coloring may be added, if desired. Makes 5 quarts.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook shells. Dice onion and bell pepper. Saute in Worcestershire sauce.
Add hamburger and brown.
Pour in tomato sauce; simmer.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup milk.
Put shells in casserole dish and cover with hamburger sauce.
Pour soup over sauce. Sprinkle lots of cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple pie
directions: Prepare apples and add sugar mixed with flour and nutmeg.
Add orange juice and butter.
Mix lightly.
Fill in 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Then in moderate oven (325°) for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Cook chicken until done; remove chicken from pot.
Put bouillon cubes and poultry seasoning in broth with margarine and food coloring.
Put buttermilk and eggs in flour and mix until it is really thick.
Using softball size amounts, knead in flour. Roll out on floured sheet until dough is thin as a pie crust.
Cut into 1 to 1 1/2 inch squares and cook in broth.
When done, add deboned and shredded chicken.

title: pickled green tomatoes
directions: Fill each sterilized jar with boiling hot brine; seal immediately.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix well. Sprinkle Chinese noodles over each serving, if desired.

title: hard lefse
directions: Beat eggs with sugar and syrup.
Mix with other ingredients, adding enough flour to handle.
Roll out thin and cook on a moderate hot plate.

title: zabagliona
directions: Beat egg yolks rapidly, adding slowly the sugar and beat well. Add slowly orange juice (squeeze juice and grate rind of orange and lemon; strain before using) or substitute 1 cup wine for orange juice.
Pour into top of double boiler and heat until double in bulk and thick, about 12 minutes.
Serve ice cold with Bing cherries, brandy or cognac over cold custard.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed. Pour into shallow greased pan. Bake in 350° oven until light brown.

title: sandcups
directions: You wil need a measuring cup, 8 to 10 paper cups, a large bowl, rolling pin, wire whisk and a zipper style plastic bag.

title: "quickie" sauerbraten
directions: Place meat in large kettle with all ingredients.
Simmer 2 or 3 hours until meat is tender.
Remove meat.
Strain gravy into large bowl.
Replace in kettle and thicken with flour and water mixture.
Slice meat and combine with thickened gravy.
Serve over noodles.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and mix in salt thoroughly.
Add grated eggs, eggs and flour.
Spray pan.
Put in batter by spoonfuls and press flat.
Fry until brown and crisp.
Rub cottage cheese through a fine sieve.
Mix in milk or cream or caraway seed.
Season with salt, if unsalted.

title: nonnie's tortellini
directions: Mix completely and knead until dough is smooth.
Let stand covered 20 minutes to rest.
Knead again for 5 minutes and let rest again for 20 minutes.
Roll out and fill with filling.

title: wicked jilly chili
directions: In a large pot, cook onion and garlic until soft.
Add ground meat and stir until just cooked.
Add all other ingredients except kidney beans.
Simmer over low heat 1/2 hour.
Add beans.
Place in casserole and bake 1/2 hour with Mozzarella cheese grated on top or simmer total 1 hour on stove top, adding beans last 15 minutes.
Serve with grated Mozzarella cheese.

title: ham, sweet potato bake
directions: Put ham in baking dish; top with pineapple ring and clove. Mix oleo and salt into potatoes.
Spoon mixture on the pineapple rings.
Mix cranberry sauce, orange peel, juice and brown sugar. Simmer; pour over potatoes.
Bake 45 minutes, basting.

title: kids can do - pink passion fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and blend well.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and put in refrigerator until completely chilled, at least 3 hours.
Serve chilled.

title: oriental cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumber slices and salt in a bowl; cover, let stand for 1 hour.
Rinse off excess moisture.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bring to boil, pour over cucumber slices; refrigerate.

title: bean and turkey soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven; bring to boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
12 cups (251 calories, 11% from fat, per 1 1/3 cup serving and 3.1 g fat).

title: ranch dressing
directions: Put mayonnaise in bowl.
Add buttermilk gradually, stirring until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and stir.

title: cardamom flavored easter bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar, salt, 2 cups of flour and cardamom in a large bowl.
Heat water and milk to 130°.
Add flour mixture and eggs; beat until smooth.
Add remainder of flour and the melted butter.
Stir by hand until stiff dough forms.
Let rest under inverted bowl for 15 minutes, then knead for 10 minutes.
Place in lightly greased bowl and let rise for 1 hour, punch down and let rise for 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in shortening.
Add onions and salt. Saute until onion is tender.
Stir in broth, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover, reduce heat, simmer 10 minutes.
Add green peppers, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Combine water and cornstarch; stir well. Gradually stir cornstarch mixture into steak mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add tomatoes and cook, stirring constantly, until thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: heavenly banana delight
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix instant pudding, condensed milk and milk together for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sweet okinawa doughnuts
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients to liquid and mix thoroughly. Drop by teaspoons into hot oil.
Fry until brown and drain.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on a cookie sheet. Bake about 12 minutes at 375.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook with onion in water until soft; drain. Add cracker crumbs, butter and almost all of cheese.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add cream and mix into squash.
Pour into buttered casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 425° until just done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: skillet zucchini and vegetables
directions: In large skillet on medium heat, saute onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Break up tomatoes.
Put in skillet.
Add zucchini, salt, sugar and pepper.
Cook uncovered 10 minutes or until liquid is reduced and zucchini is tender-crisp.
Sprinkle with parsley. Stir in.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Slightly mix sugar, oleo and evaporated milk in a glass bowl. Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
Remove and add 1 cup peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour in pie dish. Place in freezer for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: one meal cornbread
directions: Mix Jiffy corn muffin mix, eggs and milk together.
Shred hamburger with fork into mix.
Add celery, onion and cheese and mix.
Pat batter into greased dish.
Bake in 400° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions.
Add squash slices. Add corn, salt, pepper and dill weed.
Simmer until tender in covered skillet (about 20 minutes) on below medium heat.
(The dill weed makes this dish.)

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Line muffin pans with paper cups and spray with Pam.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.

title: garden beef and macaroni
directions: In saucepan, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
Stir to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 20 minutes or until done.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: white fish casserole
directions: Flake fish into sauce; place in a shallow casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix all the ingredients and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes.
Take out and while hot, punch holes in cake to absorb liquid topping.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Boil together dates, raisins, apples and water for 8 minutes. Add Crisco.
While mixture is still hot, set pan in cold water to cool.
Add flour, eggs and sweetener and add vanilla and nuts. Put in fridge to chill before dropping on greased cookie sheet by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Each cookie equals 50 calories or 1 fruit serving.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Mix 1 can of soup with sour cream, chicken and chilies.
Fry tortillas, leaving them a little soft.
Place chicken mixture in tortillas and roll.
Mix second can of chicken soup with remaining filling and spread over top of stuffed tortillas placed in a large baking dish. Grate cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until hot, approximately 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: shrimp and crab casserole
directions: Chop and mix all ingredients.
Grease casserole dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: dilly beans
directions: Cook the beans for 10 to 15 minutes. Drain and cool.
In bottom of each pint jar, place 1 head dill (small) and 1 clove of garlic.
Pack beans in jars.
Heat the vinegar, water and salt to boiling.
Pour over beans and seal.
Takes 2 to 3 weeks to dill. Repeat until all jars you desired to fix are canned.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup until melted.
Add gelatin which has been mixed with water.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 or 3 molds and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: italian anise cakes
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and shortening.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and anise oil.
Mix well.
Shape into small loaves; pat with flour and let it stand for 1 to 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Cut into 2-inch slices and return to oven for 10 minutes longer.
May be iced with colorful sprinkles.

title: donna cake
directions: Layer in pan as listed and bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: creamy beef bake
directions: Cook macaroni as directed.
Brown meat; add onions.
Add soup and milk.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, greased, put a layer of macaroni and cheese, then a layer of meat mixture.
Repeat each layer about 2 times, reserving a little of macaroni and cheese for the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: meat loaf
directions: Put ground beef in large mixing bowl.
Add tomato soup, eggs and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Add oats and onion.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put into a heavy baking dish.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese cake cupcakes
directions: Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
When smooth, pour into cupcake liners that have a vanilla wafer in the botom, round side down.
Fill 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
When cool, top with pie filling (any flavor).
Makes about 18 to 20.

title: white chili chicken
directions: Soak beans, then cook beans in chicken broth.
Add all other ingredients and heat to serving temperature.
Serve with cornbread or tortilla chips.

title: hot cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage in deep pan.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cabbage, heat but do not cook.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut meat in small pieces; put in pan with a little fat and brown good.
Add celery, onions, 2 tablespoons sauce, 2 tablespoons sugar and a little pepper.
Cook until done.
Add bean sprouts, a little thickening (1 tablespoon flour), 1 tablespoon sauce and a little water.
Garnish with noodles.

title: scottish skillet potatoes
directions: Heat
bacon
fat in a 10-inch skillet until hot.
Layer half each of the potato and onion slices in skillet.
Sprinkle with half each of the salt, pepper and parsley.	Repeat.
Add water. Cover
and	simmer	over
low
heat until potatoes are tender and liquid is absorbed, about 30 minutes.
Add water if necessary. Serves 6.
(Optional:
brown small pieces of bacon to
sprinkle on each layer.)

title: easy and quick stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry in olive oil equal amounts of onions, snow peas and mushrooms with desired soy sauce.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix beans, mushrooms and soup together.
Crumble onion rings on top after beans have baked.

title: caesar margarita salad
directions: Combine lettuce and the next 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Add Margarita Dressing; toss gently.
Serve immediately.

title: custard pudding
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Slowly add milk and vanilla. Pour into custard cups or a dish.
Bake in 325° oven until knife comes out clean, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse the red beans and pick out any bad ones.
Cover with the water and set on medium heat.
Add the ham bone and sausage.
As this cooks, add onions, bell pepper, celery, shallots and seasonings.
Lower the heat to a simmer after the beans come to a boil.
Simmer for several hours.

title: tomorrow salad
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; stir in vinegar and cook in a double boiler until it thickens.
In a large bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Mix with first mixture.
Cover and refrigerate. Serve tomorrow.

title: chess pie
directions: You can make a regular pie crust or purchase graham cracker pie crust ready made.
Cream butter and sugar, then add eggs, flour and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes to set the pie, then bake at 350° until solid.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter in a skillet and stir in brown sugar until melted. Place sliced bananas in the skillet and stir until covered with the mixture of butter and brown sugar.
Remove the skillet from flame and add dark rum.
Light the mixture and let the flame go out.
Place one scoop of vanilla ice cream in a bowl and arrange banana halves around it.
Drizzle hot sauce over the ice cream and serve immediately!
Serves 2.

title: pecan pie
directions: Stir
together
first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in
pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes
or
until a knife cuts clean.
Serves 8.
Calories per serving: 517.

title: pineapple sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot oil.
Season.
Add bouillon; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and pineapple to mixture. Cook, stirring frequently, for 10 minutes.
Blend next 5 ingredients and add to mixture.
Serve on rice.
Serves 4.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together; stir for as long as your arm can stand it. Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut the sirloin into 1 x 1/8-inch strips and cook in the butter until brown.
Add minced onion and stir.
Heat 5 minutes.
Put in a casserole.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour, hot water, bouillon cubes, Tabasco sauce, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and catsup.
Cook until thickened.
Beat in 1/2 cup sour cream.
Pour over meat and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Thin cutlets if they are very thick. Grease the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish a little.
Put a layer of cutlets, layer of Swiss cheese, then spread the cream of mushroom soup on top of the cheese and lastly, cover with stuffing mix.
Bake for about 30 to 40 minutes (depending on the thickness of cutlets) and stuffing mix is golden brown.

title: chicken chiles rellenos
directions: Reserve 8 whole chiles.
Chop remaining whole chiles.
Combine chopped whole chiles, drained chopped chiles and next 3 ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: chilly day chili
directions: In a large kettle or Dutch oven, saute onions and green pepper in oil until tender.
Add beef, stirring lightly to break up. Cover.
Simmer about 30 minutes or until meat loses color.
Add tomatoes and next five ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans.
Simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon.
In separate bowl, stir flour, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Fold this into pumpkin mix.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll towel and cake.
Cool and unroll, then frost and re-roll.
Chill and slice.
Frosting is made by mixing powdered sugar, cream cheese, butter/margarine and vanilla.

title: donna's dirt cake
directions: You will need a flowerpot and artificial flowers.

title: guacamole soup
directions: Cut avocados lengthwise into fourths.
Remove pits and peel. Place avocados, water and milk in blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until chilled. Garnish each serving with lemon slices.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix all together and top on cooled cupcakes.

title: banana cake
directions: Mash banana and soda with fork.
Put butter and sugar in bowl and cream together.
Add egg, milk, flour, baking powder and banana.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Make eggs.
Let set up in refrigerator.
Melt chocolate and dip eggs.
Place on wax paper and return to refrigerator.
Store in refrigerator.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Boil carrots 5 minutes in half cup of water.
Drain carrots, then place in buttered casserole with sauteed onion.
Mix in cheese cubes.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Combine rhubarb, water, 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon flour in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Pour into 2-quart casserole or glass cake pan.
Measure 1 cup flour, remaining sugar, wheat germ, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir well to blend.
Add milk, shortening, egg and lemon juice.
Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer on medium speed.
Drop by tablespoons onto rhubarb sauce in casserole.
Combine 2 tablespoons sugar and lemon rind. Sprinkle on dough.
Bake in preheated oven (375°) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in other ingredients.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole for 30 minutes.
If desired, shredded Velveeta cheese or American can be sprinkled on top and casserole returned to oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook fryer and debone.
Cook spaghetti.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo; saute bell pepper.
Add flour; mix.
Add milk.
Cook until just getting thick.
Add cheese (save handful to sprinkle on top).
Add cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, mushrooms, pimento, soy sauce and garlic salt; mix.
Add spaghetti; fold in chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Can save baking until the next day.
Also, freezes well.

title: ham pea soup
directions: Add all ingredients but potatoes in a large pot.
Cook on medium-high heat for 1 hour.
Stir frequently.
Add more water if needed.
Reduce to medium-low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes. Stir occasionally.
Ready in 15 more minutes.

title: salsa corn chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large saucepan.
Stir in flour and spices.
Add corn, salsa, broth and pimentos.
Bring to boil; remove from heat.
Gradually add 1/4 cup hot mixture to cream cheese in a small bowl, stirring until well blended.
Return cream cheese mixture to saucepan; stir in milk until well blended.
Cook until thoroughly heated; do not boil.
Top each serving with parsley.
Serve.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ground raisin cookies
directions: Combine sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Mix soda and boiling water; mix.
Add dry ingredients, then the chopped raisins.
Refrigerate an hour or two.
Drop by spoons on a lightly greased sheet, then press lightly with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Spoon sherbet in bowl.
Let soften a little.
Add liquid.
Add more sherbet and liquid as needed.

title: refrigerator cuke pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let the mixture stand for 1 hour at room temperature, then refrigerate.

title: marmalade
directions: Halve the fruit, scoop out the pulp and chop roughly.
Tie the pips (seeds) in muslin loosely.
Shred peel finely or coarsely as required.
Put peel, pulp and pips into a large China bowl, cover with 10 cups of water and leave overnight.

title: turkey and black bean chili(student favorite)
directions: Heat oil in heavy, large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium-low heat.
Add bell pepper, onion, carrot and garlic. Saute until tender, about 12 minutes.
Add chili powder and cumin; stir to blend.
Increase heat to medium-high and add turkey. Break up with spoon and saute until turkey is no longer pink, about three minutes.
Add beans, broth and tomato paste and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer chili until liquid thickens, stirring occasionally, about one hour.
Season with salt and pepper.
(Can be prepared a day ahead.
Cover and chill.
Reheat over medium heat before serving.)

title: easy-do pralines
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except the pecans.
Cook the mixture over a low heat until it is dissolved.
Allow the mixture to come to a soft boil.
Add the pecans and cook slowly until the candy reaches the soft-ball stage in a testing cup.
Remove from heat.
Beat until the mixture thickens.
Drop by spoonfuls onto a piece of waxed paper to cool.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
In saucepan, melt butter; saute onion and mushrooms until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and sage.

title: enchiladas
directions: Heat enchilada sauce with one can water.
Fry tortillas quickly on each side and dip in sauce.
Fill with ground beef, olives, onion and cheese.
Roll and place in large Pyrex baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Cover generously with cheese.
Bake approximately 1/2 hour at 350°, or until bubbly.

title: yummy spread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and serve on waffles or toast.

title: brown sugar ice cream
directions: Cook until mixture coats spoon the eggs, brown sugar and milk. Add vanilla, raisins and pecans. Cool mixture and pour into shallow container. Freezer.

title: collins mix
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a 1-gallon pitcher or jug. Fill with water to make a full gallon.
Shake or stir well. Yields 1 gallon.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine with other ingredients; let stand overnight.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: white cookies
directions: Mix soft; do not handle much.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet, then press down with glass dipped in sugar.

title: golden carrot slices
directions: Cook carrots in salt water until done (about 10 minutes). Drain and let cool.
Put carrots, onion and bell pepper in a 1 1/2-quart glass or plastic bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard together.
Pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Add tomato soup for thicker and tangier taste.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for several hours before serving.
Will keep good in refrigerator for several days.
Good with meats.

title: uncle steve's cherry dessert
directions: Pour cherries in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cake mix over cherries.
Spread soft butter over cake mix (pats). Top with almonds. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix thoroughly sugar and
cornstarch;
stir in half and half and margarine.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Cook slightly.
Pour into shell.
Drizzle 1 teaspoon butter
over
top
and
sprinkle
cinnamon.
Place on bottom rack of oven on broil until bubbly.

title: southwest soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and chopped onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let all simmer until warmed through out.

title: angel food cake
directions: Measure
sifted
flour.
Add
cup
sugar
and sift 4 times. Combine egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and flavorings in large bowl. Beat at
high
speed of mixer until moist soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar
in 4 additions, beating until blended after each addition.
Sift in flour
mixture
in
additions, folding in with large spoon.
Turn bowl often.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40
minutes. Cool
upside
down
on
rack.
Loosen
from
sides and remove.

title: vegetable-jello salad(tart and chock-full!)
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Add cabbage, carrots, celery and pimento.
You could stop there, but I add pecans, onion and mustard as well.
Mix everything well; place in square baking dish and chill thoroughly before serving. It's a filling salad; you will find that servings ought not to be overly large.
Serves 8 to 9; keeps well in refrigerator for leftover use.

title: country fried steak and gravy
directions: Season cubed steak or cubed venison with salt, onion powder, garlic powder and pepper.
Season flour with onion powder and pepper.
Coat steak with flour and fry in oil until brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Pour out oil and make gravy.
Add water to 3 to 4 tablespoons of flour to make 2 cups.
Whip this with a whisk as you slowly add the water to keep lumps from forming.
Loosen browned flour in pan with a fork.
Leave the browned flour in the pan; it is good in the gravy.
Add the flour and water mixture and cook, stirring constantly until it reaches a full rolling boil.
Add the steak the the gravy and simmer for a few minutes to finish cooking the steak.
Stir this often as it will stick to the bottom of the pan.
Serve over white or brown rice.
I sometimes combine white and brown rice as I cook it.
We like the taste of just a little brown rice.
(It is best to use a Dutch oven for the steak as it makes a pretty full pot.)

title: glazed carrots
directions: Wash and scrape carrots; cut in diagonal slices.
Cook, covered in small amount of water until tender.
Stir in sugar and butter; cook until carrots are coated.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: baked banana custard
directions: Peel and crush bananas.
Add 2 tablespoons of sugar, nutmeg and lime juice and mix.
Place in buttered baking dish and cover with bread crumbs.
Beat eggs and remaining sugar until smooth. Heat milk and add to egg mixture.
Pour over banana mixture and bake in 325° oven until custard is set.

title: squash puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop with tablespoon in hot oil until golden brown.

title: fresh cranberry relish
directions: Do not drain pineapple.
Wash cranberries; pick out stems and any soft berries.
Cut orange or oranges into quarters; remove large membranes and seeds.
Put cranberries and orange through food grinder, using a coarse blade, or use food processor. Combine remaining ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Let stand at least 6 hours before serving.
Keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: 3 bean bake
directions: Brown beef or turkey; set aside.
Brown bacon and onion.
Mix drained beans, bacon and beef.
Blend seasonings and add.
Bake at

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple.
Place in refrigerator for several hours, until completely congealed.

title: white layer cake
directions: Measure the first 4 ingredients.
Pour these dry ingredients together and sift the mixture six times.
In a mixing bowl put the melted butter, water or milk and flavoring.

Add 1/4 tsp. salt and cream of tarter to the egg whites and beat mixture until stiff. Sift dry ingredients into the butter mixture and beat until well blended, then fold the beaten egg whites into the flour and butter mixture.
Turn into three greased pans measuring 7-inch or into two 9-inch pans.
Bake at 375° for 30-35 minutes.

title: white bean and kale soup
directions: Place cleaned beans in large saucepan.
Add enough water to cover beans 2 inches.
Boil for 5 minutes; remove from heat. Cover; let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Heat oil in large saucepan.
Add celery, carrots, onion, garlic and ham.
Cook, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes.
Add beans, chicken broth and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, or until beans are tender.
With slotted spoon, remove 1 cup beans to bowl and mash with a potato masher.
Return beans to saucepan.
Add kale; simmer for 10 minutes, or until kale is done.
Cook pasta; drain.
Stir into soup.
If you like, serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Combine butter, honey, mustard and spices in shallow pan. Roll chicken in mixture.
Arrange in single layer.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil and drain zucchini.
Mix with soup.
Add milk.
Add onion and butter.
Put in a greased baking dish with a layer of mixture, then layers of croutons, ending with croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: mom's world's best potato salad
directions: Boil and cut up potatoes.
Add grated or chopped eggs.
In separate bowl, make sauce of vinegar, mustard, mayonnaise and sugar and mix into potatoes/eggs.
Add onion and celery, salt and pepper to taste.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and oil; beat well.
Add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheet and flatten slightly with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(May press flat with glass dipped in sugar.)
Yield:
6 dozen.

title: spinach soup
directions: Chop spinach; add to stock and press through sieve.
Heat in a double boiler; add stock and milk which have been thoroughly heated.
Add butter.
Blend all together.
Add a little whipped cream before serving.
Serve hot.

title: cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, eggs, 2/3 cup sugar and almond very thoroughly to be smooth, thick and lemon color; use mixer.
Pour into greased (short) 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use toothpick to test if done.
Cool 25 minutes.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in pot and let boil, then let stand 10 minutes.
Now, mix remaining ingredients and let stand.

title: savory oven pot roast
directions: Dust beef with seasonings and flour.
Heat oil in a heavy oven-proof bag.
Brown meat; then remove.
Brown onions and garlic lightly in pan.
Replace meat on top of onions.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° until meat is tender, about 2 1/2 hours.
When roast is done, remove parsley, celery tops and bay leaf.
Serve with pan gravy.
Makes 10 servings.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all these ingredients together and pour into a deep, unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until pie is golden brown.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients with hand mixer about 2 minutes until smooth.
Put in a greased 10-inch pie dish.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
It makes its own crust.

title: raisin bread
directions: Measure water into bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast and stir to dissolve.
Add brown sugar, salt and oil.
Add 3 cups of the flour, beating until smooth and bubbly.
Add raisins, mix well.
Gradually add, while beating, the remaining flour.
Beat until mixed.
Place on lightly floured board and knead until smooth and velvety (about 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl and brush top with oil.
Cover, let rise until double, 1 hour.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Add minced onion and cook at 250° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add cubed potatoes, 1/2 cup water and salt.
Cover and cook 30 minutes at 212°.
Add milk and celery salt, allowing to heat through 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: reception salad
directions: Mix lemon Jell-O with boiled pineapple juice.
Put in refrigerator.
When it begins to gel, add other ingredients in order given.
Allow mixture to set until firm.

title: winter's eve hot cider punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large kettle and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: rice and squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: donut holes
directions: Pinch each
biscuit
into
3 parts and drop into heated pan of	shortening
(preferably
butter Crisco), until golden brown. Drain.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Put on wax paper and chill.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add 1/2 dry ingredients, sifted.
Add mincemeat and water.
Mix well.
Add nuts and remaining dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoons onto greased cookie sheets.
Make at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 1 package Ritz crackers with 1 stick of melted margarine. Put in bottom of large casserole pan.
Alternate layers of broccoli and cheese over crumbs.
Mix together the other package of crackers with remaining stick of melted margarine.
Put over top of broccoli and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until cheese bubbles.

title: oven swiss steak(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut round steak into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge in flour and pound to tenderize.
Heat oil in a large skillet (ovenproof).
Saute celery, carrots, bell pepper, onions and garlic until tender-crisp. Remove from skillet.
Add tenderized steak pieces and brown well, a few pieces at a time.
Return vegetables and all steak pieces to skillet.
Mix basil, Kitchen Bouquet, water and tomatoes.
Add to skillet.
Cover and bake in preheated oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Add more salt, if needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups, onion and chicken; mix well.
Add mayonnaise. Place in large dish (well greased).
Prepare stuffing according to box directions, using the 1/4 cup butter on top.
Place stuffing on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: orange glazed pork chops
directions: In skillet, brown chops on both sides in a small amount of hot oil; season with salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Cover; simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until chops are done.
Remove chops to warm platter. Bring sauce to boiling and spoon over chops.
Serves 4.

title: tailgate salad bowl
directions: Bring a large pot of water to boil.
Add carrots and cook 1 minute.
Add cauliflower and broccoli, cooking 1 more minute.
Add the green beans cooking 1 more minute.
Add zucchini and cook 1 minute more.
Drain well.
Mix vegetables in a large bowl with peppers and onions.
Pour your favorite Italian or oil and vinegar dressing over mix.
Chill, stirring occasionally.

title: down-home beans and potatoes
directions: Wash beans, trim ends and remove strings.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces; set aside.
Fry bacon until crisp in a Dutch oven.
Remove bacon and set aside.
Reserve 1/4 cup bacon drippings in Dutch oven.
Saute onion in drippings until tender.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Make as pie crust; add 2 eggs, well beaten.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll into balls, place on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and milk; set aside. Blend together shortening and sugar. Add egg; beat hard. Stir in about half of the flour mixture, then stir in bananas. Add rest of flour and mix well. Spread batter evenly into a 8 inch square or loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes. Double recipe for tube pan and bake for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and 7-Up over low heat until thick. Add food coloring until color is suitable.
Pour strawberries into baked pie shell.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Chill well. Top with Cool Whip.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add water, Pet milk and beaten egg yolks. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thick, add margarine, vanilla and raisins.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Egg whites may be used for meringue.

title: apple crumb dessert
directions: Chop
apples
(peel
if preferred), set aside.	Combine flour, sugar, margarine and vanilla until well blended.
Place apples in pan
and
top
with
flour	mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy apple crisp
directions: Grease pie pan with butter and sliced apples into it to a depth of 1 to 1 1/2 inches.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and egg thoroughly.
Sprinkle mixture on apples.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over crumb mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Slice up vegetables into thin strips.
Scramble egg in margarine.
Heat wok with a tablespoon of oil; add onion and vegetable strips.
Stir until partly cooked.
Add rice, soy sauce, egg and seasonings.
Cook, stirring frequently.
After about 6 to 7 minutes, serve.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix Miracle Whip and warm water; beat well.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Add red cake coloring and flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In skillet brown onion and celery in oleo.
Add undiluted mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine all ingredients and bake in casserole for 30 minute at 350°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Dissolve baking soda into 2 cups boiling water; set aside and cool.
Cream butter and sugar together; beat in eggs.
Stir in rest of the ingredients, adding soda water last.
Bake in muffin pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Covered batter can be kept refrigerated for up to 6 weeks.

title: grape frost
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend until smooth.
Serve at once.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: fluffy jello
directions: Make jello according to box directions; put in refrigerator. When jello is soft set, make Dream Whip according to package directions.
Using mixer that you have made Dream Whip with mix or beat jello, then add Dream Whip and beat.
Put in serving dish. Use enough marshmallows to cover top.
Let set up, then serve.

title: red, white and blue fruit salad
directions: First Layer:
Dissolve 1 package raspberry jello and 1 box partially thawed frozen raspberries in 1 cup boiling water.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and let stand until firm.

title: 2 hour rolls
directions: Scald milk, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm.
Crumble in yeast and stir until dissolved. Add 3 cups flour and beat until perfectly smooth.
Add melted shortening and the remaining flour (or enough flour to make an easily handled dough).
Knead well. Place dough in greased bowl. Cover and set in warm place, free from draft.
Let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Shape into rolls and place in well-greased pans. Cover and let rise until light, about 45 minutes.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Combine berries, 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Cook until berries are soft (approximately 15 minutes).
Combine cornstarch and 3 tablespoons water; add to blueberry mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool.
Combine flour, margarine and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: cheer'em up salad(yield: 9 servings)
directions: Combine the orange and lemon gelatins.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Measure 1 cup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add cold water to the remaining gelatin.
Add pineapple with juice and carrots.
Pour into a 5 cup mold.
Chill until set, but not firm. Blend the yogurt mixture into the reserved gelatin.
Spoon into the mold.
Chill until firm (4 hours).
Unmold.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water. Stir lemon juice, then pineapple juice and cold water. Pour over ice cubes in punch bowl. Serve in punch cups. Makes about 4 1/2-quarts.

title: porcupine in casserole
directions: Combine beef, rice, onion, celery, green pepper, egg, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Form into 1 1/2-inch balls, about 18.
Place into lightly greased, shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, water and catsup; bring to a boil and pour over meat balls.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and stir in cheese spread.

title: artichoke hearts
directions: Drain and rinse artichokes.
Place in shallow baking dish. Combine butter, mayonnaise, lemon juice and celery salt.
Cook in saucepan until heated through; do not boil.
Pour over artichokes. Top with almonds and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until light brown in color.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown meat and onion in butter. Add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter, then Cool Whip. Pour into crusts. Chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1 layer of margarine, then a layer of broccoli and a layer of grated cheese.
Pour 1/2 of cream of chicken soup over the layers.
Now repeat this.
Crush the crackers and sprinkle them as the last layer.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Stir at 4 minutes. Add butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add soda.
Stir and pour immediately onto a greased cookie sheet and let cool.
After cooled, break into pieces.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream butter,
Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat
well after each one. Stir cherries into flour and add alternately
with milk.
Add flavoring.
Pour into well greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° approximately 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter
in
8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix flour, milk and sugar; add
to
melted
butter.
Add peaches, but do not stir. Bake at 375°
for
minutes
or until browning is noticed. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: pastor's favorite german chocolate butter pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients except German chocolate and chocolate chips into mixing bowl.
Beat 10 minutes with electric mixer. Fold in grated chocolate and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan 55 to 65 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken rice
directions: Stir together.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Can also lay chicken on top and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate chip butterscotch bars
directions: Combine flour and soda and set aside.
With an electric mixer, blend sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla and beat at medium speed until light and smooth.
Add the flour mixture, pecans and chocolate chips.
Blend at low speed until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Transfer mixture into 8 x 8-inch greased baking pan; smooth evenly.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean, but center is still soft.
Cool to room temperature.
Cut with sharp knife into 1 x 2-inch bars.
Yields 16 bars.

title: shoo-fly cake(crustless)
directions: Add to crumb mixture.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into a floured and greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked apple and cheese pancake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven until hot and bubbly.
Beat flour, milk, salt and eggs until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake until sides of pancake are puffed and deep golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Squeeze juice of lemon over apples.
Arrange on pancake. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: apple nut torte
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and spices into a bowl.
Make a well and add the eggs with vanilla and beat well.
Stir in the apples and nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan in a 325° oven.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a large skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain. Add salt, garlic powder, catsup and sour cream. Mix all well. Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
On ungreased cookie sheet, press or roll each biscuit to a 4 x 4-inch square. Fill with Sloppy Joe mix. Fold corner of square to form a triangle.
Seal edges with a fork. Cut 3 (1/2-inch) slits on top. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden. Brush with melted butter, if desired.
Serve while hot.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together in large serving pitcher and refrigerate. Serve as needed.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter until light and fluffy. Gradually add about half the powdered sugar, beating well.
Beat in the milk and vanilla.
Gradually add the remaining powdered sugar, beating constantly.
Beat in additional milk if necessary, to make frosting spread consistency.
Add the two 1 ounce squares of unsweetened chocolate. Melt in a saucepan and then cool.
Stir in 1/4 cup finely chopped nuts (if desired).
Frost cake.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, margarine and sugar; set aside.
In another bowl, mix pudding and milk 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Fold pudding mix into cream cheese mixture (not all at once).
Then fold in whipped topping.

title: aunt pearl's chickenetti
directions: Place chicken, green pepper, pimento and onion in casserole. Heat stock and soup, adding pepper, grated cheese and spaghetti. Pour over chicken; toss well.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Fold together the apples, celery and nuts with French dressing and serve on lettuce leaves.
With mayonnaise, serve immediately as nuts will discolor the fruits if allowed to stand long.

title: le petit dejuener(gourmet dish of eggs and mushrooms.)
directions: Cut hard-boiled eggs in half and remove yolks.
Mix egg yolks with chicken broth until desirable consistency for stuffing. Re-stuff egg whites with yolk mixture.
Place side by side in a shallow casserole.
Melt butter and add flour to make a roux. Slowly add milk, stirring constantly.
As mixture thickens, add broth.
Add mushrooms.
Cover eggs with sauce.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; work in flour and pecans, vanilla and water.
Pinch off and roll size and length of finger.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes at 300° to 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still hot after placing on wax paper.

title: cheesy chicken skillet
directions: Spray large skillet with no stick cooking spray. Add chicken; cook and stir on medium-high heat 5 minutes or until cooked through, stirring occasionally. Stir in 1 to 1 1/2 cups water, milk and macaroni. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally. Add contents of cheese sauce pouch; stir until well blended. Makes 4 servings.

title: asparagus and chicken soup
directions: Heat stock.
Cut chicken into small pieces.
After asparagus is cooked, cut into small pieces.
Save 1 cup of water to add to chicken stock.
Add chicken and boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with cold water and add to soup, stirring constantly.
Add sherry.
Slowly add beaten eggs and asparagus.
Heat through.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Grease and
flour
a
x 13-inch pan.
Bake cake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until cake tests done.	Top with Cool Whip.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan or Dutch oven, cook onion in margarine until tender; stir in flour. Gradually stir in water, then broccoli, bouillon and Worcestershire. Over medium heat, cook and stir until thickened and broccoli is tender, about 10 minutes. Add cheese and cream. Cook and stir until cheese melts and soup is hot (do not boil). Garnish as desired. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: banana-blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mashed bananas.
Fold dry ingredients into creamed mixture in a few quick stirs until almost blended.
Add blueberries and transfer immediately into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 6 Texas style muffins or 24 regular sized muffins.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes.
(Make into small balls before putting on cookie sheet.) Makes about 7 dozen cookies.

title: stump hole cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, pecans and 1 egg; mix well. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan (like a crust). Combine sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; pour on crust. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar and heat.
Add oil and salt.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour vinegar mixture over it.
Let stand for a few days.

title: cucumber sauce
directions: Grate and process cucumbers; drain and add sour cream, salt and vinegar and blend by hand.
Chill.

title: carrot coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray a square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch) with nonstick cooking spray.

Beat flours, yogurt, 2/3 cup sugar, margarine, baking powder, baking soda, ginger and egg whites in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl frequently. Beat on medium speed 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in carrot and raisins.
Spread batter in pan.

title: breakfast souffle casserole
directions: Cook sausage.
Cool.
Cut crusts from bread and cube.
Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350°.
Can be mixed the night before and put in refrigerator.

title: spanish squash
directions: Dice squash and onion.
Saute in butter until tender.
Add salt and pepper.
Add drained chilies and corn.
Place in casserole and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Serves 6 to 8.

title: confetti fish salad(185 calories per serving)
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in a 10-inch skillet over high heat in 1-inch of boiling water, heat frozen fish fillets to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer about 15 minutes, until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
With slotted spatula, remove fish to medium bowl.
Flake into small pieces. Add remaining ingredients; toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until salad is well chilled. Makes 4 main servings.

title: old settler's baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Stir slowly and gently only until dry ingredients are dampened.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add brown sugar until absorbed. (Thick.)
Sprinkle pecans over brown sugar.
Add pineapple slices. Put cherries on.
Mix cake as directed on box.
Instead of water, use the juice off the pineapple and water to correct amount.
Pour over pineapple and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until done.
Cake will be brown.
Remove from oven and turn over onto plate.

title: raspberry or strawberry cooler
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in 4 cups of water.
Add juices and chill.

title: aunt marge's broccoli salad
directions: Combine ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt and cocoa. Add 1 cup milk. Add 3 egg yolks and remaining cup of milk.
Mix and stir in saucepan until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into cooked and cooled pastry.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix cheese, mushroom soup and tomatoes.
In a baking dish, put in layer shells, chicken and mixture. Bake until tender.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk and cocoa. Cook boiling 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add peanut butter. Then add the oatmeal and mix.
Immediately spoon onto wax paper.
A small spoonful for each cookie.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Shred lettuce to cover bottom of dish (1-inch or more deep). Mix the mayonnaise with the sugar.
Layer ingredients as in the order listed.
Keep in icebox.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to serve, sprinkle bacon bits on top.

title: broccoli and cheese cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Mix other ingredients together and pour melted oleo in the mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown on top.

title: fruit slush
directions: Do not drain fruits.
Mix everything together and freeze.

title: tabbouleh
directions: Place bulgur in medium bowl and pour boiling water over it. Allow to sit for at least one hour to absorb moisture.
Drain bulgur.
Turn into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Good with pita bread.

title: lemon-chicken nuggets
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice, salt, paprika and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add chicken for 8 hours. Drain chicken.
Dredge in flour.

title: lamb chops with rosemary
directions: Crush rosemary and sage or marjoram and place in bowl with the lamb.
Add garlic and oil and allow to marinate for three hours or longer.
Place lamb chops on broiling rack and broil under high heat for 5 minutes per side.
Splash with lemon juice, salt and pepper and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: anadama bread
directions: Heat water, 1/2 cup cornmeal, salt, butter and molasses in medium size saucepan until thick and bubbly.
Pour into a large bowl; cook to lukewarm, about 45 minutes.
Sprinkle or crumble yeast into 1/2 cup very warm water in a cup.
(Very warm water should feel comfortable when dropped on wrist.)
Stir until yeast dissolves, then blend into cooled cornmeal mixture.
Beat in 2 cups of the flour until smooth.
Stir in 3 more cups.
Turn out onto a lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Knead until elastic, about 10 minutes, using remaining cup of flour as needed to keep dough from sticking.
Place dough in a greased large bowl; turn to coat all over with shortening.
Cover with a towel or Saran Wrap.
Let rise in a warm place away from draft about 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk (inside stove, if you have a pilot light, is perfect spot for letting bread rise).
Punch dough down; knead in bowl a few times.
Shape into a ball (or 2 smaller balls).
Press into a greased baking dish (or grease a cookie pan and just set balls on it).
Brush top with soft shortening. Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Let rise again in a warm place away from draft with Saran Wrap over top for 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk and cheese.
Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Top with sausage.
Pour egg mixture over sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar in 1 cup warm water.

title: sweet 'n sour cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
In a saucepan, heat 1/2 inch salted water and 2 tablespoons vinegar to boiling.
Add cabbage and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Fry bacon crisp and drain; pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Stir brown sugar and flour into fat.
Add water, vinegar, salt, pepper and onion.
Cook until it thickens (about 5 minutes).
Add bacon and sauce to cabbage.
Stir thoroughly. Serve hot.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Add all ingredients to pot of water.
Cook until soup is ready.

title: drunken chicken
directions: Clean chicken and pat dry.

Mix remaining ingredients and pour into an empty aluminum drink can such as a beer or soft drink can. Place bottom cavity of chicken over the can so that the chicken is sitting up with legs just touching grill.
Place can with chicken directly over a hot charcoal fire.
Cover grill and cook for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open the grill during the cooking.
The result should be a very moist chicken.
Several chickens can be cooked at one time like this.
Serves 3 - 4.

title: quickie cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oven while it's preheating to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine milk and vanilla with dry ingredients.
Pour into pan with butter.
Pour peaches or other fruit over the butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and bake at 400°.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Mix all the prepared ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Or it can be cooked in a heavy skillet (we use an iron one) on the top of stove.
(Really good.)

title: sally shoppers candy
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Spread liberally with butter or margarine.
Place whole crackers side by side until bottom of pan is covered.
Boil sugar and butter 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers. Bake 7 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips, swirling over entire area as they melt. Sprinkle with nuts.
Cool and cut into bars.
Keep refrigerated or freeze.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Put layer of graham crackers on foil.
Melt butter in saucepan and add brown sugar. Bring to full boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir well.
Spoon over crackers. Bake at 350 degrees for 5-10 minutes.
Oven time may vary.
Remove when edges are slightly browned.
Cool completely then break into pieces.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Cut crust off of bread slices and cut each slice into 9 pieces.
Beat egg and milk.
Dip bread pieces into egg.
Brush with melted butter and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Place on baking sheet and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole(makes 8 servings)
directions: Spread half of the dry stuffing mix in a large Pyrex baking dish. Pour chicken broth and melted butter over stuffing mix. Mix chicken, celery, onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper and spread evenly over stuffing. Pour milk and beaten eggs over casserole. Refrigerate overnight. Spread mushroom soup over casserole. Add remainder of the stuffing mix evenly to top the casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: creamy chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt.
Remove chicken from liquid; cook vegetables 10 minutes.
Add seasoning to broth and cook noodles 4 minutes.
Add butter, flour and evaporated milk and thicken.
Put chicken in.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Mix rice, butter, soup mix and water.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with pork chops.
Tightly cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Stir rice and serve.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: jelly roll
directions: Set oven at 400°.
Line bottom of pan with wax paper.
Mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and flavoring in large bowl with beater.
Beat, adding sugar gradually.
Mix hot water and butter.
Add with flour mixture all at once.
Beat about 1 minute.
Fold with spatula until airy.
Turn into pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 15 minutes until light brown.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on towel.
Place cake on towel.
Peel off paper.
Cool.
Roll up cake.
Unroll after 10 minutes and spread with jelly.
Roll up again and tuck open end under.
Sift powdered sugar on top.

title: strawberry icebox dessert
directions: Crush wafers to make crumbs.
Melt half of butter and mix with the crumbs.
Spread about 2/3 of crumbs firmly in bottom of a 9 x 3-inch pan.

title: barbecue(beef or pork)
directions: Mix and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until sauce is thickened.

title: bachelor's breakfast
directions: Preheat skillet to whatever your stove will do (high) while you get the stuff out.
Spread butter thickly on both sides of bread at least 1/8-inch thick.
Place one slice of bread in skillet, butter side down, then cheese, then the last slice of bread, butter side up.
The bottom slice should be brown by now, so turn with spatula and push down on top of sandwich with spatula.

title: robbie's chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces of almond bark in 2-quart microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries; sprinkle with coconut.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Bake in 3 round layers or 9 x 13 inch baking pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool. Frost.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar, egg and molasses thoroughly, then stir in soda dissolved in hot water.
Sift flour, salt and spices together and stir into mix.
Drop from tablespoon onto cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Frost with a mix of confectioners sugar, oleo, milk and vanilla just thick enough to spread.

title: cool cherry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes and chill for 30 minutes. Refrigerate before and after serving.

title: marshmallow creme
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a mixing bowl; set aside for 5 minutes to allow gelatin to soften.
Add to boiling water in a saucepan; cook and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cool to consistency of thick syrup.
Stir in fructose and vanilla.
Beat egg whites into soft peaks.
Very slowly trickle a small stream of gelatin mixture into egg whites, beating until all gelatin mixture is blended.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Pour into prepared pan.

title: cucumber tomato salad
directions: Slice cucumbers and bell pepper.
Chop onion, cut tomatoes in chunks.
Mix rest of ingredients and marinate vegetables until served.

title: hermits
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients, water, raisins and nuts.
Mark dough quarters in bowl. Take one quarter and roll into sausage-like roll to fit lengthwise on a greased cookie sheet, 2 rolls on a sheet.
Brush tops with beaten egg.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
Cut when cool.

title: artichoke-asparagus salad
directions: Toss ingredients and serve.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 2 tablespoons for each cup of hot water.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all together and bake uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: broccoli and tomato casserole
directions: Make a cheese sauce of butter, flour, milk, salt, cheese and onion or lemon juice.
Place broccoli, which has been cooked until tender, in bottom of casserole.
Cover with sauce.
Cut tomatoes in halves and place on top of sauce and broccoli.
Place bacon on top.
Bake until bacon is crisp.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fig cake
directions: Bake in sheet cake pan.
While cake is still hot, prepare icing.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, squash, onion, crumbs, half the cheese, butter, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well and pour in buttered casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: raisin bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Stir in 1 3/4 cup warm water, sugar, salt, oil and 3 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth. Mix in raisins and remaining flour to make dough easy to handle, then knead till smooth.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double.
Then put layers of dough, cinnamon and sugar in bread pans. (about 8x3) Bake in 400 degree oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: punch
directions: Mix juice together.
Mix in sherbet.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: banana marshmallow fluff
directions: Combine marshmallows and milk in a saucepan (or melt in microwave).
Stir over low heat until marshmallows are melted. Cool and add nuts and banana.
In a chilled bowl with chilled beaters, whip whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into banana mixture.
Pour into 4-cup melon mold or bowl.
Chill in refrigerator until firm.
Garnish with strawberries, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: scarlett o'hara(served at antoine's in new orleans)
directions: Shake with cracked ice; strain and serve.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef cubes in soup kettle.
Then add enough water to beef (2 1/2 quarts).
Add mixed vegetables, salt, potato cubes and onion.
Bring to boil and then reduce to lower heat.
Let soup cook until vegetables can be cut with a spoon.
Add beef broth and bring to a boil.
Use noodles last and boil slowly until noodles are cooked.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, chocolate syrup, flour and baking powder.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: quick pizza dip
directions: Beat soft cream cheese and Italian seasoning with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, pizza sauce and the other cup of cheese.
Sprinkle peppers over top.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350° or until mixture is thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.
Serve with breadsticks.
Preparation time:
5 minutes, cooking time, 20 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: bean soup
directions: Boil ham hocks in water in a large (10-quart or larger) pot until meat falls off the bone (about 3 to 4 hours).
Add remaining ingredients except watercress and cook for an additional hour. Watercress and/or sliced cabbage can be added the last 15 to 20 minutes of cooking time.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Chill.
Serve with fresh strawberries, sliced apples or any fresh fruit.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice angel food cake.
Put slices on dessert plate.
Spoon sweetened strawberries over cake.
Top with Cool Whip.
Spoon more strawberries on top of Cool Whip for flavor and decoration. Enjoy.

title: chock-full-of-chicken pie
directions: Pour chicken broth in a large pot.
Bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes or until noodles are soft. Serves 4.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Mix together and keep refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread chicken evenly over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking dish.
Spread soup over chicken evenly.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Add to dry stuffing mixture the broth, margarine and egg.
Spread stuffing over cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: miss cokie's chicken pie
directions: Boil fryer until tender.
Cool and remove bones.
Place in 10 x 10 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix together and cook at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Use 9-inch pie pan for Fudge Pie.
Pie is even better when served ala mode.

title: hearty supper salad(serves 6)
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Put potatoes in large bowl; add 1/4 cup dressing to hot potatoes.
Marinate several hours.
Combine Swiss cheese, salami, onion, green pepper and tomatoes in second bowl.
Add remaining 1/4 cup dressing to 2nd mixture.
Chill one hour (at least).
At serving time, drain dressing from mixtures.
Combine potatoes, meat, cheese, vegetable mixture.
Line salad bowl with crisp greens; add potato mixture. Top with mayonnaise and chopped parsley.

title: greek salad
directions: Toss all ingredients (except dressing) in large bowl.
Pour equal parts of each dressing over salad.
Toss and serve.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, pour into baked pie shell.
Bake 350 for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Boil noodles and drain.
Put in large casserole dish.
Add soup, milk, cheese, beef and onion; mix.
Crumble bread on top. Add melted butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake until bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: sunday brunch casserole
directions: Combine ham, bread crumbs, green pepper, peas, onion and rosemary in medium bowl.
Beat eggs lightly; add milk.
Pour over ham mixture.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes until blended and glossy.
Add 1/4 cup milk, 2 eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 1 1/2 minutes until smooth.
Pour into 2 well-greased, lined and floured 8-inch layer cake pan or 9 x 13 x 2 pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook ingredients until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Break up raw beef in bottom of a casserole dish.
Then put corn; add sliced onion on top of corn.
Place Tater Tots over onion.
Dilute soup with milk; pour over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: aaran's corn chip supper
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add canned tomatoes and chop into pieces.
Add beans, chili powder and cumin.
Simmer until beans are tender.
Place corn chips on plate.
Cover with chili mixture.
Top with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and taco sauce to taste.
Quick and easy supper; kid's favorite.

title: ruth's chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing, butter and broth.
Divide in half and put 1/2 in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, salt and mayonnaise together and spread over the dressing in the pan.
Beat 2 eggs slightly with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Pour evenly over casserole contents.
Cover the top with the other half of dressing. Cover pan with foil and leave overnight.
Take out 1 hour before ready to bake.
Spread 1 can of mushroom soup over top.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 325°.
Spread grated cheese on top and return to oven for 10 minutes.
Serves at least 12 or more.

title: squash fritters
